5102 /* [expr.cond]
5103
5104 If the second and third operands are glvalues of the same value
5105 category and have the same type, the result is of that type and
5106 value category. */
5107 if (((lvalue_p (arg2) && lvalue_p (arg3))
5108 || (xvalue_p (arg2) && xvalue_p (arg3)))
5109 && same_type_p (arg2_type, arg3_type))
5110 {
5111 result_type = arg2_type;
5112 arg2 = mark_lvalue_use (arg2);
5113 arg3 = mark_lvalue_use (arg3);
5114 goto valid_operands;
5115 }
5116
5117 /* [expr.cond]
5118
5119 Otherwise, the result is an rvalue. If the second and third
5120 operand do not have the same type, and either has (possibly
5121 cv-qualified) class type, overload resolution is used to
5122 determine the conversions (if any) to be applied to the operands
5123 (_over.match.oper_, _over.built_). */
5124 is_lvalue = false;
5125 if (!same_type_p (arg2_type, arg3_type)
5126 && (CLASS_TYPE_P (arg2_type) || CLASS_TYPE_P (arg3_type)))
5127 {
5128 tree args[3];
5129 conversion *conv;
5130 bool any_viable_p;
5131
5132 /* Rearrange the arguments so that add_builtin_candidate only has
5133 to know about two args. In build_builtin_candidate, the
5134 arguments are unscrambled. */
5135 args[0] = arg2;
5136 args[1] = arg3;
5137 args[2] = arg1;
5138 add_builtin_candidates (&candidates,
5139 COND_EXPR,
5140 NOP_EXPR,
5141 cp_operator_id (COND_EXPR),
5142 args,
5143 LOOKUP_NORMAL, complain);
5144
5145 /* [expr.cond]
5146
5147 If the overload resolution fails, the program is
5148 ill-formed. */
5149 candidates = splice_viable (candidates, false, &any_viable_p);
5150 if (!any_viable_p)
5151 {
5152 if (complain & tf_error)
5153 error_at (loc, "operands to ?: have different types %qT and %qT",
5154 arg2_type, arg3_type);
5155 return error_mark_node;
5156 }
5157 cand = tourney (candidates, complain);
5158 if (!cand)
5159 {
5160 if (complain & tf_error)
5161 {
5162 op_error (loc, COND_EXPR, NOP_EXPR, arg1, arg2, arg3, FALSE);
5163 print_z_candidates (loc, candidates);
5164 }
5165 return error_mark_node;
5166 }
5167
5168 /* [expr.cond]
5169
5170 Otherwise, the conversions thus determined are applied, and
5171 the converted operands are used in place of the original
5172 operands for the remainder of this section. */
5173 conv = cand->convs[0];
5174 arg1 = convert_like (conv, arg1, complain);
5175 conv = cand->convs[1];
5176 arg2 = convert_like (conv, arg2, complain);
5177 arg2_type = TREE_TYPE (arg2);
5178 conv = cand->convs[2];
5179 arg3 = convert_like (conv, arg3, complain);
5180 arg3_type = TREE_TYPE (arg3);
5181 }
5182
5183 /* [expr.cond]
5184
5185 Lvalue-to-rvalue (_conv.lval_), array-to-pointer (_conv.array_),
5186 and function-to-pointer (_conv.func_) standard conversions are
5187 performed on the second and third operands.
5188
5189 We need to force the lvalue-to-rvalue conversion here for class types,
5190 so we get TARGET_EXPRs; trying to deal with a COND_EXPR of class rvalues
5191 that isn't wrapped with a TARGET_EXPR plays havoc with exception
5192 regions. */
5193
5194 arg2 = force_rvalue (arg2, complain);
5195 if (!CLASS_TYPE_P (arg2_type))
5196 arg2_type = TREE_TYPE (arg2);
5197
5198 arg3 = force_rvalue (arg3, complain);
5199 if (!CLASS_TYPE_P (arg3_type))
5200 arg3_type = TREE_TYPE (arg3);
5201
5202 if (arg2 == error_mark_node || arg3 == error_mark_node)
5203 return error_mark_node;
5204
5205 /* [expr.cond]
5206
5207 After those conversions, one of the following shall hold:
5208
5209 --The second and third operands have the same type; the result is of
5210 that type. */
5211 if (same_type_p (arg2_type, arg3_type))
5212 result_type = arg2_type;
5213 /* [expr.cond]
5214
5215 --The second and third operands have arithmetic or enumeration
5216 type; the usual arithmetic conversions are performed to bring
5217 them to a common type, and the result is of that type. */
5218 else if ((ARITHMETIC_TYPE_P (arg2_type)
5219 || UNSCOPED_ENUM_P (arg2_type))
5220 && (ARITHMETIC_TYPE_P (arg3_type)
5221 || UNSCOPED_ENUM_P (arg3_type)))
5222 {
5223 /* In this case, there is always a common type. */
5224 result_type = type_after_usual_arithmetic_conversions (arg2_type,
5225 arg3_type);
5226 if (complain & tf_warning)
5227 do_warn_double_promotion (result_type, arg2_type, arg3_type,
5228 "implicit conversion from %qT to %qT to "
5229 "match other result of conditional",
5230 loc);
5231
5232 if (TREE_CODE (arg2_type) == ENUMERAL_TYPE
5233 && TREE_CODE (arg3_type) == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
5234 {
5235 if (TREE_CODE (orig_arg2) == CONST_DECL
5236 && TREE_CODE (orig_arg3) == CONST_DECL
5237 && DECL_CONTEXT (orig_arg2) == DECL_CONTEXT (orig_arg3))
5238 /* Two enumerators from the same enumeration can have different
5239 types when the enumeration is still being defined. */;
5240 else if (complain & tf_warning)
5241 warning_at (loc, OPT_Wenum_compare, "enumeral mismatch in "
5242 "conditional expression: %qT vs %qT",
5243 arg2_type, arg3_type);
5244 }
5245 else if (extra_warnings
5246 && ((TREE_CODE (arg2_type) == ENUMERAL_TYPE
5247 && !same_type_p (arg3_type, type_promotes_to (arg2_type)))
5248 || (TREE_CODE (arg3_type) == ENUMERAL_TYPE
5249 && !same_type_p (arg2_type,
5250 type_promotes_to (arg3_type)))))
5251 {
5252 if (complain & tf_warning)
5253 warning_at (loc, OPT_Wextra, "enumeral and non-enumeral type in "
5254 "conditional expression");
5255 }
5256
5257 arg2 = perform_implicit_conversion (result_type, arg2, complain);
5258 arg3 = perform_implicit_conversion (result_type, arg3, complain);
5259 }
5260 /* [expr.cond]
5261
5262 --The second and third operands have pointer type, or one has
5263 pointer type and the other is a null pointer constant; pointer
5264 conversions (_conv.ptr_) and qualification conversions
5265 (_conv.qual_) are performed to bring them to their composite
5266 pointer type (_expr.rel_). The result is of the composite
5267 pointer type.
5268
5269 --The second and third operands have pointer to member type, or
5270 one has pointer to member type and the other is a null pointer
5271 constant; pointer to member conversions (_conv.mem_) and
5272 qualification conversions (_conv.qual_) are performed to bring
5273 them to a common type, whose cv-qualification shall match the
5274 cv-qualification of either the second or the third operand.
5275 The result is of the common type. */
5276 else if ((null_ptr_cst_p (arg2)
5277 && TYPE_PTR_OR_PTRMEM_P (arg3_type))
5278 || (null_ptr_cst_p (arg3)
5279 && TYPE_PTR_OR_PTRMEM_P (arg2_type))
5280 || (TYPE_PTR_P (arg2_type) && TYPE_PTR_P (arg3_type))
5281 || (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (arg2_type) && TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (arg3_type))
5282 || (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (arg2_type) && TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (arg3_type)))
5283 {
5284 result_type = composite_pointer_type (arg2_type, arg3_type, arg2,
5285 arg3, CPO_CONDITIONAL_EXPR,
5286 complain);
5287 if (result_type == error_mark_node)
5288 return error_mark_node;
5289 arg2 = perform_implicit_conversion (result_type, arg2, complain);
5290 arg3 = perform_implicit_conversion (result_type, arg3, complain);
5291 }
5292
5293 if (!result_type)
5294 {
5295 if (complain & tf_error)
5296 error_at (loc, "operands to ?: have different types %qT and %qT",
5297 arg2_type, arg3_type);
5298 return error_mark_node;
5299 }
5300
5301 if (arg2 == error_mark_node || arg3 == error_mark_node)
5302 return error_mark_node;
5303
5304 valid_operands:
5305 result = build3_loc (loc, COND_EXPR, result_type, arg1, arg2, arg3);
5306
5307 /* If the ARG2 and ARG3 are the same and don't have side-effects,
5308 warn here, because the COND_EXPR will be turned into ARG2. */
5309 if (warn_duplicated_branches
5310 && (arg2 == arg3 || operand_equal_p (arg2, arg3, 0)))
5311 warning_at (EXPR_LOCATION (result), OPT_Wduplicated_branches,
5312 "this condition has identical branches");
5313
5314 /* We can't use result_type below, as fold might have returned a
5315 throw_expr. */
5316
5317 if (!is_lvalue)
5318 {
5319 /* Expand both sides into the same slot, hopefully the target of
5320 the ?: expression. We used to check for TARGET_EXPRs here,
5321 but now we sometimes wrap them in NOP_EXPRs so the test would
5322 fail. */
5323 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (result)))
5324 result = get_target_expr_sfinae (result, complain);
5325 /* If this expression is an rvalue, but might be mistaken for an
5326 lvalue, we must add a NON_LVALUE_EXPR. */
5327 result = rvalue (result);
5328 }
5329 else
5330 result = force_paren_expr (result);
5331
5332 return result;
5333}
5334
5335/* Wrapper for above. */
5336
5337tree
5338build_conditional_expr (location_t loc, tree arg1, tree arg2, tree arg3,
5339 tsubst_flags_t complain)
5340{
5341 tree ret;
5342 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_OVERLOAD);
5343 ret = build_conditional_expr_1 (loc, arg1, arg2, arg3, complain);
5344 timevar_cond_stop (TV_OVERLOAD, subtime);
5345 return ret;
5346}
5347
5348/* OPERAND is an operand to an expression. Perform necessary steps
5349 required before using it. If OPERAND is NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE is
5350 returned. */
5351
5352static tree
5353prep_operand (tree operand)
5354{
5355 if (operand)
5356 {
5357 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (operand))
5358 && CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (TREE_TYPE (operand)))
5359 /* Make sure the template type is instantiated now. */
5360 instantiate_class_template (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (operand)));
5361 }
5362
5363 return operand;
5364}
5365
5366/* Add each of the viable functions in FNS (a FUNCTION_DECL or
5367 OVERLOAD) to the CANDIDATES, returning an updated list of
5368 CANDIDATES. The ARGS are the arguments provided to the call;
5369 if FIRST_ARG is non-null it is the implicit object argument,
5370 otherwise the first element of ARGS is used if needed. The
5371 EXPLICIT_TARGS are explicit template arguments provided.
5372 TEMPLATE_ONLY is true if only template functions should be
5373 considered. CONVERSION_PATH, ACCESS_PATH, and FLAGS are as for
5374 add_function_candidate. */
5375
5376static void
5377add_candidates (tree fns, tree first_arg, const vec<tree, va_gc> *args,
5378 tree return_type,
5379 tree explicit_targs, bool template_only,
5380 tree conversion_path, tree access_path,
5381 int flags,
5382 struct z_candidate **candidates,
5383 tsubst_flags_t complain)
5384{
5385 tree ctype;
5386 const vec<tree, va_gc> *non_static_args;
5387 bool check_list_ctor;
5388 bool check_converting;
5389 unification_kind_t strict;
5390 tree fn;
5391
5392 if (!fns)
5393 return;
5394
5395 /* Precalculate special handling of constructors and conversion ops. */
5396 fn = OVL_CURRENT (fns);
5397 if (DECL_CONV_FN_P (fn))
5398 {
5399 check_list_ctor = false;
5400 check_converting = !!(flags & LOOKUP_ONLYCONVERTING);
5401 if (flags & LOOKUP_NO_CONVERSION)
5402 /* We're doing return_type(x). */
5403 strict = DEDUCE_CONV;
5404 else
5405 /* We're doing x.operator return_type(). */
5406 strict = DEDUCE_EXACT;
5407 /* [over.match.funcs] For conversion functions, the function
5408 is considered to be a member of the class of the implicit
5409 object argument for the purpose of defining the type of
5410 the implicit object parameter. */
5411 ctype = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (first_arg));
5412 }
5413 else
5414 {
5415 if (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (fn))
5416 {
5417 check_list_ctor = !!(flags & LOOKUP_LIST_ONLY);
5418 /* For list-initialization we consider explicit constructors
5419 and complain if one is chosen. */
5420 check_converting
5421 = ((flags & (LOOKUP_ONLYCONVERTING|LOOKUP_LIST_INIT_CTOR))
5422 == LOOKUP_ONLYCONVERTING);
5423 }
5424 else
5425 {
5426 check_list_ctor = false;
5427 check_converting = false;
5428 }
5429 strict = DEDUCE_CALL;
5430 ctype = conversion_path ? BINFO_TYPE (conversion_path) : NULL_TREE;
5431 }
5432
5433 if (first_arg)
5434 non_static_args = args;
5435 else
5436 /* Delay creating the implicit this parameter until it is needed. */
5437 non_static_args = NULL;
5438
5439 for (; fns; fns = OVL_NEXT (fns))
5440 {
5441 tree fn_first_arg;
5442 const vec<tree, va_gc> *fn_args;
5443
5444 fn = OVL_CURRENT (fns);
5445
5446 if (check_converting && DECL_NONCONVERTING_P (fn))
5447 continue;
5448 if (check_list_ctor && !is_list_ctor (fn))
5449 continue;
5450
5451 /* Figure out which set of arguments to use. */
5452 if (DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P (fn))
5453 {
5454 /* If this function is a non-static member and we didn't get an
5455 implicit object argument, move it out of args. */
5456 if (first_arg == NULL_TREE)
5457 {
5458 unsigned int ix;
5459 tree arg;
5460 vec<tree, va_gc> *tempvec;
5461 vec_alloc (tempvec, args->length () - 1);
5462 for (ix = 1; args->iterate (ix, &arg); ++ix)
5463 tempvec->quick_push (arg);
5464 non_static_args = tempvec;
5465 first_arg = (*args)[0];
5466 }
5467
5468 fn_first_arg = first_arg;
5469 fn_args = non_static_args;
5470 }
5471 else
5472 {
5473 /* Otherwise, just use the list of arguments provided. */
5474 fn_first_arg = NULL_TREE;
5475 fn_args = args;
5476 }
5477
5478 if (TREE_CODE (fn) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
5479 add_template_candidate (candidates,
5480 fn,
5481 ctype,
5482 explicit_targs,
5483 fn_first_arg,
5484 fn_args,
5485 return_type,
5486 access_path,
5487 conversion_path,
5488 flags,
5489 strict,
5490 complain);
5491 else if (!template_only)
5492 add_function_candidate (candidates,
5493 fn,
5494 ctype,
5495 fn_first_arg,
5496 fn_args,
5497 access_path,
5498 conversion_path,
5499 flags,
5500 complain);
5501 }
5502}
5503
5504/* Returns 1 if P0145R2 says that the LHS of operator CODE is evaluated first,
5505 -1 if the RHS is evaluated first, or 0 if the order is unspecified. */
5506
5507static int
5508op_is_ordered (tree_code code)
5509{
5510 switch (code)
5511 {
5512 // 5. b @= a
5513 case MODIFY_EXPR:
5514 return (flag_strong_eval_order > 1 ? -1 : 0);
5515
5516 // 6. a[b]
5517 case ARRAY_REF:
5518 return (flag_strong_eval_order > 1 ? 1 : 0);
5519
5520 // 1. a.b
5521 // Not overloadable (yet).
5522 // 2. a->b
5523 // Only one argument.
5524 // 3. a->*b
5525 case MEMBER_REF:
5526 // 7. a << b
5527 case LSHIFT_EXPR:
5528 // 8. a >> b
5529 case RSHIFT_EXPR:
5530 return (flag_strong_eval_order ? 1 : 0);
5531
5532 default:
5533 return 0;
5534 }
5535}
5536
5537static tree
5538build_new_op_1 (location_t loc, enum tree_code code, int flags, tree arg1,
5539 tree arg2, tree arg3, tree *overload, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5540{
5541 struct z_candidate *candidates = 0, *cand;
5542 vec<tree, va_gc> *arglist;
5543 tree fnname;
5544 tree args[3];
5545 tree result = NULL_TREE;
5546 bool result_valid_p = false;
5547 enum tree_code code2 = NOP_EXPR;
5548 enum tree_code code_orig_arg1 = ERROR_MARK;
5549 enum tree_code code_orig_arg2 = ERROR_MARK;
5550 conversion *conv;
5551 void *p;
5552 bool strict_p;
5553 bool any_viable_p;
5554
5555 if (error_operand_p (arg1)
5556 || error_operand_p (arg2)
5557 || error_operand_p (arg3))
5558 return error_mark_node;
5559
5560 if (code == MODIFY_EXPR)
5561 {
5562 code2 = TREE_CODE (arg3);
5563 arg3 = NULL_TREE;
5564 fnname = cp_assignment_operator_id (code2);
5565 }
5566 else
5567 fnname = cp_operator_id (code);
5568
5569 arg1 = prep_operand (arg1);
5570
5571 bool memonly = false;
5572 switch (code)
5573 {
5574 case NEW_EXPR:
5575 case VEC_NEW_EXPR:
5576 case VEC_DELETE_EXPR:
5577 case DELETE_EXPR:
5578 /* Use build_op_new_call and build_op_delete_call instead. */
5579 gcc_unreachable ();
5580
5581 case CALL_EXPR:
5582 /* Use build_op_call instead. */
5583 gcc_unreachable ();
5584
5585 case TRUTH_ORIF_EXPR:
5586 case TRUTH_ANDIF_EXPR:
5587 case TRUTH_AND_EXPR:
5588 case TRUTH_OR_EXPR:
5589 /* These are saved for the sake of warn_logical_operator. */
5590 code_orig_arg1 = TREE_CODE (arg1);
5591 code_orig_arg2 = TREE_CODE (arg2);
5592 break;
5593 case GT_EXPR:
5594 case LT_EXPR:
5595 case GE_EXPR:
5596 case LE_EXPR:
5597 case EQ_EXPR:
5598 case NE_EXPR:
5599 /* These are saved for the sake of maybe_warn_bool_compare. */
5600 code_orig_arg1 = TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg1));
5601 code_orig_arg2 = TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg2));
5602 break;
5603
5604 /* =, ->, [], () must be non-static member functions. */
5605 case MODIFY_EXPR:
5606 if (code2 != NOP_EXPR)
5607 break;
5608 /* FALLTHRU */
5609 case COMPONENT_REF:
5610 case ARRAY_REF:
5611 memonly = true;
5612 break;
5613
5614 default:
5615 break;
5616 }
5617
5618 arg2 = prep_operand (arg2);
5619 arg3 = prep_operand (arg3);
5620
5621 if (code == COND_EXPR)
5622 /* Use build_conditional_expr instead. */
5623 gcc_unreachable ();
5624 else if (! OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg1))
5625 && (! arg2 || ! OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg2))))
5626 goto builtin;
5627
5628 if (code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR || code == POSTDECREMENT_EXPR)
5629 arg2 = integer_zero_node;
5630
5631 vec_alloc (arglist, 3);
5632 arglist->quick_push (arg1);
5633 if (arg2 != NULL_TREE)
5634 arglist->quick_push (arg2);
5635 if (arg3 != NULL_TREE)
5636 arglist->quick_push (arg3);
5637
5638 /* Get the high-water mark for the CONVERSION_OBSTACK. */
5639 p = conversion_obstack_alloc (0);
5640
5641 /* Add namespace-scope operators to the list of functions to
5642 consider. */
5643 if (!memonly)
5644 add_candidates (lookup_function_nonclass (fnname, arglist,
5645 /*block_p=*/true),
5646 NULL_TREE, arglist, NULL_TREE,
5647 NULL_TREE, false, NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE,
5648 flags, &candidates, complain);
5649
5650 args[0] = arg1;
5651 args[1] = arg2;
5652 args[2] = NULL_TREE;
5653
5654 /* Add class-member operators to the candidate set. */
5655 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg1)))
5656 {
5657 tree fns;
5658
5659 fns = lookup_fnfields (TREE_TYPE (arg1), fnname, 1);
5660 if (fns == error_mark_node)
5661 {
5662 result = error_mark_node;
5663 goto user_defined_result_ready;
5664 }
5665 if (fns)
5666 add_candidates (BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (fns),
5667 NULL_TREE, arglist, NULL_TREE,
5668 NULL_TREE, false,
5669 BASELINK_BINFO (fns),
5670 BASELINK_ACCESS_BINFO (fns),
5671 flags, &candidates, complain);
5672 }
5673 /* Per 13.3.1.2/3, 2nd bullet, if no operand has a class type, then
5674 only non-member functions that have type T1 or reference to
5675 cv-qualified-opt T1 for the first argument, if the first argument
5676 has an enumeration type, or T2 or reference to cv-qualified-opt
5677 T2 for the second argument, if the second argument has an
5678 enumeration type. Filter out those that don't match. */
5679 else if (! arg2 || ! CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (arg2)))
5680 {
5681 struct z_candidate **candp, **next;
5682
5683 for (candp = &candidates; *candp; candp = next)
5684 {
5685 tree parmlist, parmtype;
5686 int i, nargs = (arg2 ? 2 : 1);
5687
5688 cand = *candp;
5689 next = &cand->next;
5690
5691 parmlist = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (cand->fn));
5692
5693 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i)
5694 {
5695 parmtype = TREE_VALUE (parmlist);
5696
5697 if (TREE_CODE (parmtype) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
5698 parmtype = TREE_TYPE (parmtype);
5699 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (args[i])) == ENUMERAL_TYPE
5700 && (same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p
5701 (TREE_TYPE (args[i]), parmtype)))
5702 break;
5703
5704 parmlist = TREE_CHAIN (parmlist);
5705 }
5706
5707 /* No argument has an appropriate type, so remove this
5708 candidate function from the list. */
5709 if (i == nargs)
5710 {
5711 *candp = cand->next;
5712 next = candp;
5713 }
5714 }
5715 }
5716
5717 add_builtin_candidates (&candidates, code, code2, fnname, args,
5718 flags, complain);
5719
5720 switch (code)
5721 {
5722 case COMPOUND_EXPR:
5723 case ADDR_EXPR:
5724 /* For these, the built-in candidates set is empty
5725 [over.match.oper]/3. We don't want non-strict matches
5726 because exact matches are always possible with built-in
5727 operators. The built-in candidate set for COMPONENT_REF
5728 would be empty too, but since there are no such built-in
5729 operators, we accept non-strict matches for them. */
5730 strict_p = true;
5731 break;
5732
5733 default:
5734 strict_p = false;
5735 break;
5736 }
5737
5738 candidates = splice_viable (candidates, strict_p, &any_viable_p);
5739 if (!any_viable_p)
5740 {
5741 switch (code)
5742 {
5743 case POSTINCREMENT_EXPR:
5744 case POSTDECREMENT_EXPR:
5745 /* Don't try anything fancy if we're not allowed to produce
5746 errors. */
5747 if (!(complain & tf_error))
5748 return error_mark_node;
5749
5750 /* Look for an `operator++ (int)'. Pre-1985 C++ didn't
5751 distinguish between prefix and postfix ++ and
5752 operator++() was used for both, so we allow this with
5753 -fpermissive. */
5754 else
5755 {
5756 const char *msg = (flag_permissive)
5757 ? G_("no %<%D(int)%> declared for postfix %qs,"
5758 " trying prefix operator instead")
5759 : G_("no %<%D(int)%> declared for postfix %qs");
5760 permerror (loc, msg, fnname, operator_name_info[code].name);
5761 }
5762
5763 if (!flag_permissive)
5764 return error_mark_node;
5765
5766 if (code == POSTINCREMENT_EXPR)
5767 code = PREINCREMENT_EXPR;
5768 else
5769 code = PREDECREMENT_EXPR;
5770 result = build_new_op_1 (loc, code, flags, arg1, NULL_TREE,
5771 NULL_TREE, overload, complain);
5772 break;
5773
5774 /* The caller will deal with these. */
5775 case ADDR_EXPR:
5776 case COMPOUND_EXPR:
5777 case COMPONENT_REF:
5778 result = NULL_TREE;
5779 result_valid_p = true;
5780 break;
5781
5782 default:
5783 if (complain & tf_error)
5784 {
5785 /* If one of the arguments of the operator represents
5786 an invalid use of member function pointer, try to report
5787 a meaningful error ... */
5788 if (invalid_nonstatic_memfn_p (loc, arg1, tf_error)
5789 || invalid_nonstatic_memfn_p (loc, arg2, tf_error)
5790 || invalid_nonstatic_memfn_p (loc, arg3, tf_error))
5791 /* We displayed the error message. */;
5792 else
5793 {
5794 /* ... Otherwise, report the more generic
5795 "no matching operator found" error */
5796 op_error (loc, code, code2, arg1, arg2, arg3, FALSE);
5797 print_z_candidates (loc, candidates);
5798 }
5799 }
5800 result = error_mark_node;
5801 break;
5802 }
5803 }
5804 else
5805 {
5806 cand = tourney (candidates, complain);
5807 if (cand == 0)
5808 {
5809 if (complain & tf_error)
5810 {
5811 op_error (loc, code, code2, arg1, arg2, arg3, TRUE);
5812 print_z_candidates (loc, candidates);
5813 }
5814 result = error_mark_node;
5815 }
5816 else if (TREE_CODE (cand->fn) == FUNCTION_DECL)
5817 {
5818 if (overload)
5819 *overload = cand->fn;
5820
5821 if (resolve_args (arglist, complain) == NULL)
5822 result = error_mark_node;
5823 else
5824 result = build_over_call (cand, LOOKUP_NORMAL, complain);
5825
5826 if (trivial_fn_p (cand->fn))
5827 /* There won't be a CALL_EXPR. */;
5828 else if (result && result != error_mark_node)
5829 {
5830 tree call = extract_call_expr (result);
5831 CALL_EXPR_OPERATOR_SYNTAX (call) = true;
5832
5833 if (processing_template_decl && DECL_HIDDEN_FRIEND_P (cand->fn))
5834 /* This prevents build_new_function_call from discarding this
5835 function during instantiation of the enclosing template. */
5836 KOENIG_LOOKUP_P (call) = 1;
5837
5838 /* Specify evaluation order as per P0145R2. */
5839 CALL_EXPR_ORDERED_ARGS (call) = false;
5840 switch (op_is_ordered (code))
5841 {
5842 case -1:
5843 CALL_EXPR_REVERSE_ARGS (call) = true;
5844 break;
5845
5846 case 1:
5847 CALL_EXPR_ORDERED_ARGS (call) = true;
5848 break;
5849
5850 default:
5851 break;
5852 }
5853 }
5854 }
5855 else
5856 {
5857 /* Give any warnings we noticed during overload resolution. */
5858 if (cand->warnings && (complain & tf_warning))
5859 {
5860 struct candidate_warning *w;
5861 for (w = cand->warnings; w; w = w->next)
5862 joust (cand, w->loser, 1, complain);
5863 }
5864
5865 /* Check for comparison of different enum types. */
5866 switch (code)
5867 {
5868 case GT_EXPR:
5869 case LT_EXPR:
5870 case GE_EXPR:
5871 case LE_EXPR:
5872 case EQ_EXPR:
5873 case NE_EXPR:
5874 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg1)) == ENUMERAL_TYPE
5875 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (arg2)) == ENUMERAL_TYPE
5876 && (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (arg1))
5877 != TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (arg2)))
5878 && (complain & tf_warning))
5879 {
5880 warning (OPT_Wenum_compare,
5881 "comparison between %q#T and %q#T",
5882 TREE_TYPE (arg1), TREE_TYPE (arg2));
5883 }
5884 break;
5885 default:
5886 break;
5887 }
5888
5889 /* We need to strip any leading REF_BIND so that bitfields
5890 don't cause errors. This should not remove any important
5891 conversions, because builtins don't apply to class
5892 objects directly. */
5893 conv = cand->convs[0];
5894 if (conv->kind == ck_ref_bind)
5895 conv = next_conversion (conv);
5896 arg1 = convert_like (conv, arg1, complain);
5897
5898 if (arg2)
5899 {
5900 conv = cand->convs[1];
5901 if (conv->kind == ck_ref_bind)
5902 conv = next_conversion (conv);
5903 else
5904 arg2 = decay_conversion (arg2, complain);
5905
5906 /* We need to call warn_logical_operator before
5907 converting arg2 to a boolean_type, but after
5908 decaying an enumerator to its value. */
5909 if (complain & tf_warning)
5910 warn_logical_operator (loc, code, boolean_type_node,
5911 code_orig_arg1, arg1,
5912 code_orig_arg2, arg2);
5913
5914 arg2 = convert_like (conv, arg2, complain);
5915 }
5916 if (arg3)
5917 {
5918 conv = cand->convs[2];
5919 if (conv->kind == ck_ref_bind)
5920 conv = next_conversion (conv);
5921 arg3 = convert_like (conv, arg3, complain);
5922 }
5923
5924 }
5925 }
5926
5927 user_defined_result_ready:
5928
5929 /* Free all the conversions we allocated. */
5930 obstack_free (&conversion_obstack, p);
5931
5932 if (result || result_valid_p)
5933 return result;
5934
5935 builtin:
5936 switch (code)
5937 {
5938 case MODIFY_EXPR:
5939 return cp_build_modify_expr (loc, arg1, code2, arg2, complain);
5940
5941 case INDIRECT_REF:
5942 return cp_build_indirect_ref (arg1, RO_UNARY_STAR, complain);
5943
5944 case TRUTH_ANDIF_EXPR:
5945 case TRUTH_ORIF_EXPR:
5946 case TRUTH_AND_EXPR:
5947 case TRUTH_OR_EXPR:
5948 if (complain & tf_warning)
5949 warn_logical_operator (loc, code, boolean_type_node,
5950 code_orig_arg1, arg1,
5951 code_orig_arg2, arg2);
5952 /* Fall through. */
5953 case GT_EXPR:
5954 case LT_EXPR:
5955 case GE_EXPR:
5956 case LE_EXPR:
5957 case EQ_EXPR:
5958 case NE_EXPR:
5959 if ((complain & tf_warning)
5960 && ((code_orig_arg1 == BOOLEAN_TYPE)
5961 ^ (code_orig_arg2 == BOOLEAN_TYPE)))
5962 maybe_warn_bool_compare (loc, code, arg1, arg2);
5963 if (complain & tf_warning && warn_tautological_compare)
5964 warn_tautological_cmp (loc, code, arg1, arg2);
5965 /* Fall through. */
5966 case PLUS_EXPR:
5967 case MINUS_EXPR:
5968 case MULT_EXPR:
5969 case TRUNC_DIV_EXPR:
5970 case MAX_EXPR:
5971 case MIN_EXPR:
5972 case LSHIFT_EXPR:
5973 case RSHIFT_EXPR:
5974 case TRUNC_MOD_EXPR:
5975 case BIT_AND_EXPR:
5976 case BIT_IOR_EXPR:
5977 case BIT_XOR_EXPR:
5978 return cp_build_binary_op (loc, code, arg1, arg2, complain);
5979
5980 case UNARY_PLUS_EXPR:
5981 case NEGATE_EXPR:
5982 case BIT_NOT_EXPR:
5983 case TRUTH_NOT_EXPR:
5984 case PREINCREMENT_EXPR:
5985 case POSTINCREMENT_EXPR:
5986 case PREDECREMENT_EXPR:
5987 case POSTDECREMENT_EXPR:
5988 case REALPART_EXPR:
5989 case IMAGPART_EXPR:
5990 case ABS_EXPR:
5991 return cp_build_unary_op (code, arg1, candidates != 0, complain);
5992
5993 case ARRAY_REF:
5994 return cp_build_array_ref (input_location, arg1, arg2, complain);
5995
5996 case MEMBER_REF:
5997 return build_m_component_ref (cp_build_indirect_ref (arg1, RO_ARROW_STAR,
5998 complain),
5999 arg2, complain);
6000
6001 /* The caller will deal with these. */
6002 case ADDR_EXPR:
6003 case COMPONENT_REF:
6004 case COMPOUND_EXPR:
6005 return NULL_TREE;
6006
6007 default:
6008 gcc_unreachable ();
6009 }
6010 return NULL_TREE;
6011}
6012
6013/* Wrapper for above. */
6014
6015tree
6016build_new_op (location_t loc, enum tree_code code, int flags,
6017 tree arg1, tree arg2, tree arg3,
6018 tree *overload, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6019{
6020 tree ret;
6021 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_OVERLOAD);
6022 ret = build_new_op_1 (loc, code, flags, arg1, arg2, arg3,
6023 overload, complain);
6024 timevar_cond_stop (TV_OVERLOAD, subtime);
6025 return ret;
6026}
6027
6028/* CALL was returned by some call-building function; extract the actual
6029 CALL_EXPR from any bits that have been tacked on, e.g. by
6030 convert_from_reference. */
6031
6032tree
6033extract_call_expr (tree call)
6034{
6035 while (TREE_CODE (call) == COMPOUND_EXPR)
6036 call = TREE_OPERAND (call, 1);
6037 if (REFERENCE_REF_P (call))
6038 call = TREE_OPERAND (call, 0);
6039 if (TREE_CODE (call) == TARGET_EXPR)
6040 call = TARGET_EXPR_INITIAL (call);
6041 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (call) == CALL_EXPR
6042 || TREE_CODE (call) == AGGR_INIT_EXPR
6043 || call == error_mark_node);
6044 return call;
6045}
6046
6047/* Returns true if FN has two parameters, of which the second has type
6048 size_t. */
6049
6050static bool
6051second_parm_is_size_t (tree fn)
6052{
6053 tree t = FUNCTION_ARG_CHAIN (fn);
6054 if (!t || !same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (t), size_type_node))
6055 return false;
6056 t = TREE_CHAIN (t);
6057 if (t == void_list_node)
6058 return true;
6059 if (aligned_new_threshold && t
6060 && same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (t), align_type_node)
6061 && TREE_CHAIN (t) == void_list_node)
6062 return true;
6063 return false;
6064}
6065
6066/* True if T, an allocation function, has std::align_val_t as its second
6067 argument. */
6068
6069bool
6070aligned_allocation_fn_p (tree t)
6071{
6072 if (!aligned_new_threshold)
6073 return false;
6074
6075 tree a = FUNCTION_ARG_CHAIN (t);
6076 return (a && same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (a), align_type_node));
6077}
6078
6079/* Returns true iff T, an element of an OVERLOAD chain, is a usual deallocation
6080 function (3.7.4.2 [basic.stc.dynamic.deallocation]) with a parameter of
6081 std::align_val_t. */
6082
6083static bool
6084aligned_deallocation_fn_p (tree t)
6085{
6086 if (!aligned_new_threshold)
6087 return false;
6088
6089 /* A template instance is never a usual deallocation function,
6090 regardless of its signature. */
6091 if (TREE_CODE (t) == TEMPLATE_DECL
6092 || primary_template_instantiation_p (t))
6093 return false;
6094
6095 tree a = FUNCTION_ARG_CHAIN (t);
6096 if (same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (a), align_type_node)
6097 && TREE_CHAIN (a) == void_list_node)
6098 return true;
6099 if (!same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (a), size_type_node))
6100 return false;
6101 a = TREE_CHAIN (a);
6102 if (a && same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (a), align_type_node)
6103 && TREE_CHAIN (a) == void_list_node)
6104 return true;
6105 return false;
6106}
6107
6108/* Returns true iff T, an element of an OVERLOAD chain, is a usual
6109 deallocation function (3.7.4.2 [basic.stc.dynamic.deallocation]). */
6110
6111bool
6112usual_deallocation_fn_p (tree t)
6113{
6114 /* A template instance is never a usual deallocation function,
6115 regardless of its signature. */
6116 if (TREE_CODE (t) == TEMPLATE_DECL
6117 || primary_template_instantiation_p (t))
6118 return false;
6119
6120 /* If a class T has a member deallocation function named operator delete
6121 with exactly one parameter, then that function is a usual
6122 (non-placement) deallocation function. If class T does not declare
6123 such an operator delete but does declare a member deallocation
6124 function named operator delete with exactly two parameters, the second
6125 of which has type std::size_t (18.2), then this function is a usual
6126 deallocation function. */
6127 bool global = DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (t);
6128 tree chain = FUNCTION_ARG_CHAIN (t);
6129 if (!chain)
6130 return false;
6131 if (chain == void_list_node
6132 || ((!global || flag_sized_deallocation)
6133 && second_parm_is_size_t (t)))
6134 return true;
6135 if (aligned_deallocation_fn_p (t))
6136 return true;
6137 return false;
6138}
6139
6140/* Build a call to operator delete. This has to be handled very specially,
6141 because the restrictions on what signatures match are different from all
6142 other call instances. For a normal delete, only a delete taking (void *)
6143 or (void *, size_t) is accepted. For a placement delete, only an exact
6144 match with the placement new is accepted.
6145
6146 CODE is either DELETE_EXPR or VEC_DELETE_EXPR.
6147 ADDR is the pointer to be deleted.
6148 SIZE is the size of the memory block to be deleted.
6149 GLOBAL_P is true if the delete-expression should not consider
6150 class-specific delete operators.
6151 PLACEMENT is the corresponding placement new call, or NULL_TREE.
6152
6153 If this call to "operator delete" is being generated as part to
6154 deallocate memory allocated via a new-expression (as per [expr.new]
6155 which requires that if the initialization throws an exception then
6156 we call a deallocation function), then ALLOC_FN is the allocation
6157 function. */
6158
6159tree
6160build_op_delete_call (enum tree_code code, tree addr, tree size,
6161 bool global_p, tree placement,
6162 tree alloc_fn, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6163{
6164 tree fn = NULL_TREE;
6165 tree fns, fnname, type, t;
6166
6167 if (addr == error_mark_node)
6168 return error_mark_node;
6169
6170 type = strip_array_types (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (addr)));
6171
6172 fnname = cp_operator_id (code);
6173
6174 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type)
6175 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (complete_type (type))
6176 && !global_p)
6177 /* In [class.free]
6178
6179 If the result of the lookup is ambiguous or inaccessible, or if
6180 the lookup selects a placement deallocation function, the
6181 program is ill-formed.
6182
6183 Therefore, we ask lookup_fnfields to complain about ambiguity. */
6184 {
6185 fns = lookup_fnfields (TYPE_BINFO (type), fnname, 1);
6186 if (fns == error_mark_node)
6187 return error_mark_node;
6188 }
6189 else
6190 fns = NULL_TREE;
6191
6192 if (fns == NULL_TREE)
6193 fns = lookup_name_nonclass (fnname);
6194
6195 /* Strip const and volatile from addr. */
6196 addr = cp_convert (ptr_type_node, addr, complain);
6197
6198 if (placement)
6199 {
6200 /* "A declaration of a placement deallocation function matches the
6201 declaration of a placement allocation function if it has the same
6202 number of parameters and, after parameter transformations (8.3.5),
6203 all parameter types except the first are identical."
6204
6205 So we build up the function type we want and ask instantiate_type
6206 to get it for us. */
6207 t = FUNCTION_ARG_CHAIN (alloc_fn);
6208 t = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, ptr_type_node, t);
6209 t = build_function_type (void_type_node, t);
6210
6211 fn = instantiate_type (t, fns, tf_none);
6212 if (fn == error_mark_node)
6213 return NULL_TREE;
6214
6215 if (BASELINK_P (fn))
6216 fn = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (fn);
6217
6218 /* "If the lookup finds the two-parameter form of a usual deallocation
6219 function (3.7.4.2) and that function, considered as a placement
6220 deallocation function, would have been selected as a match for the
6221 allocation function, the program is ill-formed." */
6222 if (second_parm_is_size_t (fn))
6223 {
6224 const char *const msg1
6225 = G_("exception cleanup for this placement new selects "
6226 "non-placement operator delete");
6227 const char *const msg2
6228 = G_("%qD is a usual (non-placement) deallocation "
6229 "function in C++14 (or with -fsized-deallocation)");
6230
6231 /* But if the class has an operator delete (void *), then that is
6232 the usual deallocation function, so we shouldn't complain
6233 about using the operator delete (void *, size_t). */
6234 if (DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (fn))
6235 for (t = BASELINK_P (fns) ? BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (fns) : fns;
6236 t; t = OVL_NEXT (t))
6237 {
6238 tree elt = OVL_CURRENT (t);
6239 if (usual_deallocation_fn_p (elt)
6240 && FUNCTION_ARG_CHAIN (elt) == void_list_node)
6241 goto ok;
6242 }
6243 /* Before C++14 a two-parameter global deallocation function is
6244 always a placement deallocation function, but warn if
6245 -Wc++14-compat. */
6246 else if (!flag_sized_deallocation)
6247 {
6248 if ((complain & tf_warning)
6249 && warning (OPT_Wc__14_compat, msg1))
6250 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn), msg2, fn);
6251 goto ok;
6252 }
6253
6254 if (complain & tf_warning_or_error)
6255 {
6256 if (permerror (input_location, msg1))
6257 {
6258 /* Only mention C++14 for namespace-scope delete. */
6259 if (DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (fn))
6260 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn), msg2, fn);
6261 else
6262 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn),
6263 "%qD is a usual (non-placement) deallocation "
6264 "function", fn);
6265 }
6266 }
6267 else
6268 return error_mark_node;
6269 ok:;
6270 }
6271 }
6272 else
6273 /* "Any non-placement deallocation function matches a non-placement
6274 allocation function. If the lookup finds a single matching
6275 deallocation function, that function will be called; otherwise, no
6276 deallocation function will be called." */
6277 for (t = BASELINK_P (fns) ? BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (fns) : fns;
6278 t; t = OVL_NEXT (t))
6279 {
6280 tree elt = OVL_CURRENT (t);
6281 if (usual_deallocation_fn_p (elt))
6282 {
6283 if (!fn)
6284 {
6285 fn = elt;
6286 continue;
6287 }
6288
6289 /* -- If the type has new-extended alignment, a function with a
6290 parameter of type std::align_val_t is preferred; otherwise a
6291 function without such a parameter is preferred. If exactly one
6292 preferred function is found, that function is selected and the
6293 selection process terminates. If more than one preferred
6294 function is found, all non-preferred functions are eliminated
6295 from further consideration. */
6296 if (aligned_new_threshold)
6297 {
6298 bool want_align = type_has_new_extended_alignment (type);
6299 bool fn_align = aligned_deallocation_fn_p (fn);
6300 bool elt_align = aligned_deallocation_fn_p (elt);
6301
6302 if (elt_align != fn_align)
6303 {
6304 if (want_align == elt_align)
6305 fn = elt;
6306 continue;
6307 }
6308 }
6309
6310 /* -- If the deallocation functions have class scope, the one
6311 without a parameter of type std::size_t is selected. */
6312 bool want_size;
6313 if (DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (fn))
6314 want_size = false;
6315
6316 /* -- If the type is complete and if, for the second alternative
6317 (delete array) only, the operand is a pointer to a class type
6318 with a non-trivial destructor or a (possibly multi-dimensional)
6319 array thereof, the function with a parameter of type std::size_t
6320 is selected.
6321
6322 -- Otherwise, it is unspecified whether a deallocation function
6323 with a parameter of type std::size_t is selected. */
6324 else
6325 {
6326 want_size = COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type);
6327 if (code == VEC_DELETE_EXPR
6328 && !TYPE_VEC_NEW_USES_COOKIE (type))
6329 /* We need a cookie to determine the array size. */
6330 want_size = false;
6331 }
6332 bool fn_size = second_parm_is_size_t (fn);
6333 bool elt_size = second_parm_is_size_t (elt);
6334 gcc_assert (fn_size != elt_size);
6335 if (want_size == elt_size)
6336 fn = elt;
6337 }
6338 }
6339
6340 /* If we have a matching function, call it. */
6341 if (fn)
6342 {
6343 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (fn) == FUNCTION_DECL);
6344
6345 /* If the FN is a member function, make sure that it is
6346 accessible. */
6347 if (BASELINK_P (fns))
6348 perform_or_defer_access_check (BASELINK_BINFO (fns), fn, fn,
6349 complain);
6350
6351 /* Core issue 901: It's ok to new a type with deleted delete. */
6352 if (DECL_DELETED_FN (fn) && alloc_fn)
6353 return NULL_TREE;
6354
6355 if (placement)
6356 {
6357 /* The placement args might not be suitable for overload
6358 resolution at this point, so build the call directly. */
6359 int nargs = call_expr_nargs (placement);
6360 tree *argarray = XALLOCAVEC (tree, nargs);
6361 int i;
6362 argarray[0] = addr;
6363 for (i = 1; i < nargs; i++)
6364 argarray[i] = CALL_EXPR_ARG (placement, i);
6365 if (!mark_used (fn, complain) && !(complain & tf_error))
6366 return error_mark_node;
6367 return build_cxx_call (fn, nargs, argarray, complain);
6368 }
6369 else
6370 {
6371 tree ret;
6372 vec<tree, va_gc> *args = make_tree_vector ();
6373 args->quick_push (addr);
6374 if (second_parm_is_size_t (fn))
6375 args->quick_push (size);
6376 if (aligned_deallocation_fn_p (fn))
6377 {
6378 tree al = build_int_cst (align_type_node, TYPE_ALIGN_UNIT (type));
6379 args->quick_push (al);
6380 }
6381 ret = cp_build_function_call_vec (fn, &args, complain);
6382 release_tree_vector (args);
6383 return ret;
6384 }
6385 }
6386
6387 /* [expr.new]
6388
6389 If no unambiguous matching deallocation function can be found,
6390 propagating the exception does not cause the object's memory to
6391 be freed. */
6392 if (alloc_fn)
6393 {
6394 if ((complain & tf_warning)
6395 && !placement)
6396 warning (0, "no corresponding deallocation function for %qD",
6397 alloc_fn);
6398 return NULL_TREE;
6399 }
6400
6401 if (complain & tf_error)
6402 error ("no suitable %<operator %s%> for %qT",
6403 operator_name_info[(int)code].name, type);
6404 return error_mark_node;
6405}
6406
6407/* If the current scope isn't allowed to access DECL along
6408 BASETYPE_PATH, give an error. The most derived class in
6409 BASETYPE_PATH is the one used to qualify DECL. DIAG_DECL is
6410 the declaration to use in the error diagnostic. */
6411
6412bool
6413enforce_access (tree basetype_path, tree decl, tree diag_decl,
6414 tsubst_flags_t complain)
6415{
6416 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (basetype_path) == TREE_BINFO);
6417
6418 if (flag_new_inheriting_ctors
6419 && DECL_INHERITED_CTOR (decl))
6420 {
6421 /* 7.3.3/18: The additional constructors are accessible if they would be
6422 accessible when used to construct an object of the corresponding base
6423 class. */
6424 decl = strip_inheriting_ctors (decl);
6425 basetype_path = lookup_base (basetype_path, DECL_CONTEXT (decl),
6426 ba_any, NULL, complain);
6427 }
6428
6429 if (!accessible_p (basetype_path, decl, true))
6430 {
6431 if (complain & tf_error)
6432 {
6433 if (flag_new_inheriting_ctors)
6434 diag_decl = strip_inheriting_ctors (diag_decl);
6435 if (TREE_PRIVATE (decl))
6436 {
6437 error ("%q#D is private within this context", diag_decl);
6438 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (diag_decl),
6439 "declared private here");
6440 }
6441 else if (TREE_PROTECTED (decl))
6442 {
6443 error ("%q#D is protected within this context", diag_decl);
6444 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (diag_decl),
6445 "declared protected here");
6446 }
6447 else
6448 {
6449 error ("%q#D is inaccessible within this context", diag_decl);
6450 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (diag_decl), "declared here");
6451 }
6452 }
6453 return false;
6454 }
6455
6456 return true;
6457}
6458
6459/* Initialize a temporary of type TYPE with EXPR. The FLAGS are a
6460 bitwise or of LOOKUP_* values. If any errors are warnings are
6461 generated, set *DIAGNOSTIC_FN to "error" or "warning",
6462 respectively. If no diagnostics are generated, set *DIAGNOSTIC_FN
6463 to NULL. */
6464
6465static tree
6466build_temp (tree expr, tree type, int flags,
6467 diagnostic_t *diagnostic_kind, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6468{
6469 int savew, savee;
6470 vec<tree, va_gc> *args;
6471
6472 *diagnostic_kind = DK_UNSPECIFIED;
6473
6474 /* If the source is a packed field, calling the copy constructor will require
6475 binding the field to the reference parameter to the copy constructor, and
6476 we'll end up with an infinite loop. If we can use a bitwise copy, then
6477 do that now. */
6478 if ((lvalue_kind (expr) & clk_packed)
6479 && CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (expr))
6480 && !type_has_nontrivial_copy_init (TREE_TYPE (expr)))
6481 return get_target_expr_sfinae (expr, complain);
6482
6483 savew = warningcount + werrorcount, savee = errorcount;
6484 args = make_tree_vector_single (expr);
6485 expr = build_special_member_call (NULL_TREE, complete_ctor_identifier,
6486 &args, type, flags, complain);
6487 release_tree_vector (args);
6488 if (warningcount + werrorcount > savew)
6489 *diagnostic_kind = DK_WARNING;
6490 else if (errorcount > savee)
6491 *diagnostic_kind = DK_ERROR;
6492 return expr;
6493}
6494
6495/* Perform warnings about peculiar, but valid, conversions from/to NULL.
6496 EXPR is implicitly converted to type TOTYPE.
6497 FN and ARGNUM are used for diagnostics. */
6498
6499static void
6500conversion_null_warnings (tree totype, tree expr, tree fn, int argnum)
6501{
6502 /* Issue warnings about peculiar, but valid, uses of NULL. */
6503 if (expr == null_node && TREE_CODE (totype) != BOOLEAN_TYPE
6504 && ARITHMETIC_TYPE_P (totype))
6505 {
6506 source_location loc =
6507 expansion_point_location_if_in_system_header (input_location);
6508
6509 if (fn)
6510 warning_at (loc, OPT_Wconversion_null,
6511 "passing NULL to non-pointer argument %P of %qD",
6512 argnum, fn);
6513 else
6514 warning_at (loc, OPT_Wconversion_null,
6515 "converting to non-pointer type %qT from NULL", totype);
6516 }
6517
6518 /* Issue warnings if "false" is converted to a NULL pointer */
6519 else if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (expr)) == BOOLEAN_TYPE
6520 && TYPE_PTR_P (totype))
6521 {
6522 if (fn)
6523 warning_at (input_location, OPT_Wconversion_null,
6524 "converting %<false%> to pointer type for argument %P "
6525 "of %qD", argnum, fn);
6526 else
6527 warning_at (input_location, OPT_Wconversion_null,
6528 "converting %<false%> to pointer type %qT", totype);
6529 }
6530}
6531
6532/* We gave a diagnostic during a conversion. If this was in the second
6533 standard conversion sequence of a user-defined conversion sequence, say
6534 which user-defined conversion. */
6535
6536static void
6537maybe_print_user_conv_context (conversion *convs)
6538{
6539 if (convs->user_conv_p)
6540 for (conversion *t = convs; t; t = next_conversion (t))
6541 if (t->kind == ck_user)
6542 {
6543 print_z_candidate (0, " after user-defined conversion:",
6544 t->cand);
6545 break;
6546 }
6547}
6548
6549/* Perform the conversions in CONVS on the expression EXPR. FN and
6550 ARGNUM are used for diagnostics. ARGNUM is zero based, -1
6551 indicates the `this' argument of a method. INNER is nonzero when
6552 being called to continue a conversion chain. It is negative when a
6553 reference binding will be applied, positive otherwise. If
6554 ISSUE_CONVERSION_WARNINGS is true, warnings about suspicious
6555 conversions will be emitted if appropriate. If C_CAST_P is true,
6556 this conversion is coming from a C-style cast; in that case,
6557 conversions to inaccessible bases are permitted. */
6558
6559static tree
6560convert_like_real (conversion *convs, tree expr, tree fn, int argnum,
6561 int inner, bool issue_conversion_warnings,
6562 bool c_cast_p, tsubst_flags_t complain)
6563{
6564 tree totype = convs->type;
6565 diagnostic_t diag_kind;
6566 int flags;
6567 location_t loc = EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (expr, input_location);
6568
6569 if (convs->bad_p && !(complain & tf_error))
6570 return error_mark_node;
6571
6572 if (convs->bad_p
6573 && convs->kind != ck_user
6574 && convs->kind != ck_list
6575 && convs->kind != ck_ambig
6576 && (convs->kind != ck_ref_bind
6577 || (convs->user_conv_p && next_conversion (convs)->bad_p))
6578 && (convs->kind != ck_rvalue
6579 || SCALAR_TYPE_P (totype))
6580 && convs->kind != ck_base)
6581 {
6582 bool complained = false;
6583 conversion *t = convs;
6584
6585 /* Give a helpful error if this is bad because of excess braces. */
6586 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (expr)
6587 && SCALAR_TYPE_P (totype)
6588 && CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (expr) > 0
6589 && BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (expr, 0)->value))
6590 {
6591 complained = permerror (loc, "too many braces around initializer "
6592 "for %qT", totype);
6593 while (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (expr)
6594 && CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (expr) == 1)
6595 expr = CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (expr, 0)->value;
6596 }
6597
6598 /* Give a helpful error if this is bad because a conversion to bool
6599 from std::nullptr_t requires direct-initialization. */
6600 if (NULLPTR_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (expr))
6601 && TREE_CODE (totype) == BOOLEAN_TYPE)
6602 complained = permerror (loc, "converting to %qT from %qT requires "
6603 "direct-initialization",
6604 totype, TREE_TYPE (expr));
6605
6606 for (; t ; t = next_conversion (t))
6607 {
6608 if (t->kind == ck_user && t->cand->reason)
6609 {
6610 complained = permerror (loc, "invalid user-defined conversion "
6611 "from %qT to %qT", TREE_TYPE (expr),
6612 totype);
6613 if (complained)
6614 print_z_candidate (loc, "candidate is:", t->cand);
6615 expr = convert_like_real (t, expr, fn, argnum, 1,
6616 /*issue_conversion_warnings=*/false,
6617 /*c_cast_p=*/false,
6618 complain);
6619 if (convs->kind == ck_ref_bind)
6620 expr = convert_to_reference (totype, expr, CONV_IMPLICIT,
6621 LOOKUP_NORMAL, NULL_TREE,
6622 complain);
6623 else
6624 expr = cp_convert (totype, expr, complain);
6625 if (complained && fn)
6626 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn),
6627 " initializing argument %P of %qD", argnum, fn);
6628 return expr;
6629 }
6630 else if (t->kind == ck_user || !t->bad_p)
6631 {
6632 expr = convert_like_real (t, expr, fn, argnum, 1,
6633 /*issue_conversion_warnings=*/false,
6634 /*c_cast_p=*/false,
6635 complain);
6636 break;
6637 }
6638 else if (t->kind == ck_ambig)
6639 return convert_like_real (t, expr, fn, argnum, 1,
6640 /*issue_conversion_warnings=*/false,
6641 /*c_cast_p=*/false,
6642 complain);
6643 else if (t->kind == ck_identity)
6644 break;
6645 }
6646 if (!complained)
6647 complained = permerror (loc, "invalid conversion from %qT to %qT",
6648 TREE_TYPE (expr), totype);
6649 if (complained && fn)
6650 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn),
6651 " initializing argument %P of %qD", argnum, fn);
6652
6653 return cp_convert (totype, expr, complain);
6654 }
6655
6656 if (issue_conversion_warnings && (complain & tf_warning))
6657 conversion_null_warnings (totype, expr, fn, argnum);
6658
6659 switch (convs->kind)
6660 {
6661 case ck_user:
6662 {
6663 struct z_candidate *cand = convs->cand;
6664
6665 if (cand == NULL)
6666 /* We chose the surrogate function from add_conv_candidate, now we
6667 actually need to build the conversion. */
6668 cand = build_user_type_conversion_1 (totype, expr,
6669 LOOKUP_NO_CONVERSION, complain);
6670
6671 tree convfn = cand->fn;
6672
6673 /* When converting from an init list we consider explicit
6674 constructors, but actually trying to call one is an error. */
6675 if (DECL_NONCONVERTING_P (convfn) && DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (convfn)
6676 && BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (expr)
6677 /* Unless this is for direct-list-initialization. */
6678 && !CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT (expr)
6679 /* And in C++98 a default constructor can't be explicit. */
6680 && cxx_dialect >= cxx11)
6681 {
6682 if (!(complain & tf_error))
6683 return error_mark_node;
6684 location_t loc = location_of (expr);
6685 if (CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (expr) == 0
6686 && FUNCTION_FIRST_USER_PARMTYPE (convfn) != void_list_node)
6687 {
6688 if (pedwarn (loc, 0, "converting to %qT from initializer list "
6689 "would use explicit constructor %qD",
6690 totype, convfn))
6691 inform (loc, "in C++11 and above a default constructor "
6692 "can be explicit");
6693 }
6694 else
6695 error ("converting to %qT from initializer list would use "
6696 "explicit constructor %qD", totype, convfn);
6697 }
6698
6699 /* If we're initializing from {}, it's value-initialization. */
6700 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (expr)
6701 && CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (expr) == 0
6702 && TYPE_HAS_DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTOR (totype))
6703 {
6704 bool direct = CONSTRUCTOR_IS_DIRECT_INIT (expr);
6705 expr = build_value_init (totype, complain);
6706 expr = get_target_expr_sfinae (expr, complain);
6707 if (expr != error_mark_node)
6708 {
6709 TARGET_EXPR_LIST_INIT_P (expr) = true;
6710 TARGET_EXPR_DIRECT_INIT_P (expr) = direct;
6711 }
6712 return expr;
6713 }
6714
6715 expr = mark_rvalue_use (expr);
6716
6717 /* Pass LOOKUP_NO_CONVERSION so rvalue/base handling knows not to allow
6718 any more UDCs. */
6719 expr = build_over_call (cand, LOOKUP_NORMAL|LOOKUP_NO_CONVERSION,
6720 complain);
6721
6722 /* If this is a constructor or a function returning an aggr type,
6723 we need to build up a TARGET_EXPR. */
6724 if (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (convfn))
6725 {
6726 expr = build_cplus_new (totype, expr, complain);
6727
6728 /* Remember that this was list-initialization. */
6729 if (convs->check_narrowing && expr != error_mark_node)
6730 TARGET_EXPR_LIST_INIT_P (expr) = true;
6731 }
6732
6733 return expr;
6734 }
6735 case ck_identity:
6736 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (expr))
6737 {
6738 int nelts = CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (expr);
6739 if (nelts == 0)
6740 expr = build_value_init (totype, complain);
6741 else if (nelts == 1)
6742 expr = CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (expr, 0)->value;
6743 else
6744 gcc_unreachable ();
6745 }
6746 expr = mark_rvalue_use (expr);
6747
6748 if (type_unknown_p (expr))
6749 expr = instantiate_type (totype, expr, complain);
6750 /* Convert a constant to its underlying value, unless we are
6751 about to bind it to a reference, in which case we need to
6752 leave it as an lvalue. */
6753 if (inner >= 0)
6754 {
6755 expr = scalar_constant_value (expr);
6756 if (expr == null_node && INTEGRAL_OR_UNSCOPED_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (totype))
6757 /* If __null has been converted to an integer type, we do not
6758 want to warn about uses of EXPR as an integer, rather than
6759 as a pointer. */
6760 expr = build_int_cst (totype, 0);
6761 }
6762 return expr;
6763 case ck_ambig:
6764 /* We leave bad_p off ck_ambig because overload resolution considers
6765 it valid, it just fails when we try to perform it. So we need to
6766 check complain here, too. */
6767 if (complain & tf_error)
6768 {
6769 /* Call build_user_type_conversion again for the error. */
6770 build_user_type_conversion (totype, convs->u.expr, LOOKUP_IMPLICIT,
6771 complain);
6772 if (fn)
6773 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn),
6774 " initializing argument %P of %qD", argnum, fn);
6775 }
6776 return error_mark_node;
6777
6778 case ck_list:
6779 {
6780 /* Conversion to std::initializer_list<T>. */
6781 tree elttype = TREE_VEC_ELT (CLASSTYPE_TI_ARGS (totype), 0);
6782 tree new_ctor = build_constructor (init_list_type_node, NULL);
6783 unsigned len = CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (expr);
6784 tree array, val, field;
6785 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *vec = NULL;
6786 unsigned ix;
6787
6788 /* Convert all the elements. */
6789 FOR_EACH_CONSTRUCTOR_VALUE (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (expr), ix, val)
6790 {
6791 tree sub = convert_like_real (convs->u.list[ix], val, fn, argnum,
6792 1, false, false, complain);
6793 if (sub == error_mark_node)
6794 return sub;
6795 if (!BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (val)
6796 && !check_narrowing (TREE_TYPE (sub), val, complain))
6797 return error_mark_node;
6798 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (new_ctor), NULL_TREE, sub);
6799 if (!TREE_CONSTANT (sub))
6800 TREE_CONSTANT (new_ctor) = false;
6801 }
6802 /* Build up the array. */
6803 elttype = cp_build_qualified_type
6804 (elttype, cp_type_quals (elttype) | TYPE_QUAL_CONST);
6805 array = build_array_of_n_type (elttype, len);
6806 array = finish_compound_literal (array, new_ctor, complain);
6807 /* Take the address explicitly rather than via decay_conversion
6808 to avoid the error about taking the address of a temporary. */
6809 array = cp_build_addr_expr (array, complain);
6810 array = cp_convert (build_pointer_type (elttype), array, complain);
6811 if (array == error_mark_node)
6812 return error_mark_node;
6813
6814 /* Build up the initializer_list object. */
6815 totype = complete_type (totype);
6816 field = next_initializable_field (TYPE_FIELDS (totype));
6817 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (vec, field, array);
6818 field = next_initializable_field (DECL_CHAIN (field));
6819 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (vec, field, size_int (len));
6820 new_ctor = build_constructor (totype, vec);
6821 return get_target_expr_sfinae (new_ctor, complain);
6822 }
6823
6824 case ck_aggr:
6825 if (TREE_CODE (totype) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
6826 {
6827 tree real = CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (expr, 0)->value;
6828 tree imag = CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (expr, 1)->value;
6829 real = perform_implicit_conversion (TREE_TYPE (totype),
6830 real, complain);
6831 imag = perform_implicit_conversion (TREE_TYPE (totype),
6832 imag, complain);
6833 expr = build2 (COMPLEX_EXPR, totype, real, imag);
6834 return expr;
6835 }
6836 expr = reshape_init (totype, expr, complain);
6837 expr = get_target_expr_sfinae (digest_init (totype, expr, complain),
6838 complain);
6839 if (expr != error_mark_node)
6840 TARGET_EXPR_LIST_INIT_P (expr) = true;
6841 return expr;
6842
6843 default:
6844 break;
6845 };
6846
6847 expr = convert_like_real (next_conversion (convs), expr, fn, argnum,
6848 convs->kind == ck_ref_bind ? -1 : 1,
6849 convs->kind == ck_ref_bind ? issue_conversion_warnings : false,
6850 c_cast_p,
6851 complain);
6852 if (expr == error_mark_node)
6853 return error_mark_node;
6854
6855 switch (convs->kind)
6856 {
6857 case ck_rvalue:
6858 expr = decay_conversion (expr, complain);
6859 if (expr == error_mark_node)
6860 {
6861 if (complain & tf_error)
6862 {
6863 maybe_print_user_conv_context (convs);
6864 if (fn)
6865 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn),
6866 " initializing argument %P of %qD", argnum, fn);
6867 }
6868 return error_mark_node;
6869 }
6870
6871 if (! MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (totype))
6872 return expr;
6873
6874 /* Don't introduce copies when passing arguments along to the inherited
6875 constructor. */
6876 if (current_function_decl
6877 && flag_new_inheriting_ctors
6878 && DECL_INHERITED_CTOR (current_function_decl))
6879 return expr;
6880
6881 if (TREE_CODE (expr) == TARGET_EXPR
6882 && TARGET_EXPR_LIST_INIT_P (expr))
6883 /* Copy-list-initialization doesn't actually involve a copy. */
6884 return expr;
6885
6886 /* Fall through. */
6887 case ck_base:
6888 if (convs->kind == ck_base && !convs->need_temporary_p)
6889 {
6890 /* We are going to bind a reference directly to a base-class
6891 subobject of EXPR. */
6892 /* Build an expression for `*((base*) &expr)'. */
6893 expr = convert_to_base (expr, totype,
6894 !c_cast_p, /*nonnull=*/true, complain);
6895 return expr;
6896 }
6897
6898 /* Copy-initialization where the cv-unqualified version of the source
6899 type is the same class as, or a derived class of, the class of the
6900 destination [is treated as direct-initialization]. [dcl.init] */
6901 flags = LOOKUP_NORMAL;
6902 if (convs->user_conv_p)
6903 /* This conversion is being done in the context of a user-defined
6904 conversion (i.e. the second step of copy-initialization), so
6905 don't allow any more. */
6906 flags |= LOOKUP_NO_CONVERSION;
6907 else
6908 flags |= LOOKUP_ONLYCONVERTING;
6909 if (convs->rvaluedness_matches_p)
6910 flags |= LOOKUP_PREFER_RVALUE;
6911 expr = build_temp (expr, totype, flags, &diag_kind, complain);
6912 if (diag_kind && complain)
6913 {
6914 maybe_print_user_conv_context (convs);
6915 if (fn)
6916 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn),
6917 " initializing argument %P of %qD", argnum, fn);
6918 }
6919
6920 return build_cplus_new (totype, expr, complain);
6921
6922 case ck_ref_bind:
6923 {
6924 tree ref_type = totype;
6925
6926 if (convs->bad_p && !next_conversion (convs)->bad_p)
6927 {
6928 tree extype = TREE_TYPE (expr);
6929 if (TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (ref_type)
6930 && lvalue_p (expr))
6931 error_at (loc, "cannot bind rvalue reference of type %qT to "
6932 "lvalue of type %qT", totype, extype);
6933 else if (!TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (ref_type) && !lvalue_p (expr)
6934 && !CP_TYPE_CONST_NON_VOLATILE_P (TREE_TYPE (ref_type)))
6935 error_at (loc, "cannot bind non-const lvalue reference of "
6936 "type %qT to an rvalue of type %qT", totype, extype);
6937 else if (!reference_compatible_p (TREE_TYPE (totype), extype))
6938 error_at (loc, "binding reference of type %qT to %qT "
6939 "discards qualifiers", totype, extype);
6940 else
6941 gcc_unreachable ();
6942 maybe_print_user_conv_context (convs);
6943 if (fn)
6944 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn),
6945 " initializing argument %P of %qD", argnum, fn);
6946 return error_mark_node;
6947 }
6948
6949 /* If necessary, create a temporary.
6950
6951 VA_ARG_EXPR and CONSTRUCTOR expressions are special cases
6952 that need temporaries, even when their types are reference
6953 compatible with the type of reference being bound, so the
6954 upcoming call to cp_build_addr_expr doesn't fail. */
6955 if (convs->need_temporary_p
6956 || TREE_CODE (expr) == CONSTRUCTOR
6957 || TREE_CODE (expr) == VA_ARG_EXPR)
6958 {
6959 /* Otherwise, a temporary of type "cv1 T1" is created and
6960 initialized from the initializer expression using the rules
6961 for a non-reference copy-initialization (8.5). */
6962
6963 tree type = TREE_TYPE (ref_type);
6964 cp_lvalue_kind lvalue = lvalue_kind (expr);
6965
6966 gcc_assert (same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p
6967 (type, next_conversion (convs)->type));
6968 if (!CP_TYPE_CONST_NON_VOLATILE_P (type)
6969 && !TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (ref_type))
6970 {
6971 /* If the reference is volatile or non-const, we
6972 cannot create a temporary. */
6973 if (lvalue & clk_bitfield)
6974 error_at (loc, "cannot bind bitfield %qE to %qT",
6975 expr, ref_type);
6976 else if (lvalue & clk_packed)
6977 error_at (loc, "cannot bind packed field %qE to %qT",
6978 expr, ref_type);
6979 else
6980 error_at (loc, "cannot bind rvalue %qE to %qT",
6981 expr, ref_type);
6982 return error_mark_node;
6983 }
6984 /* If the source is a packed field, and we must use a copy
6985 constructor, then building the target expr will require
6986 binding the field to the reference parameter to the
6987 copy constructor, and we'll end up with an infinite
6988 loop. If we can use a bitwise copy, then we'll be
6989 OK. */
6990 if ((lvalue & clk_packed)
6991 && CLASS_TYPE_P (type)
6992 && type_has_nontrivial_copy_init (type))
6993 {
6994 error_at (loc, "cannot bind packed field %qE to %qT",
6995 expr, ref_type);
6996 return error_mark_node;
6997 }
6998 if (lvalue & clk_bitfield)
6999 {
7000 expr = convert_bitfield_to_declared_type (expr);
7001 expr = fold_convert (type, expr);
7002 }
7003 expr = build_target_expr_with_type (expr, type, complain);
7004 }
7005
7006 /* Take the address of the thing to which we will bind the
7007 reference. */
7008 expr = cp_build_addr_expr (expr, complain);
7009 if (expr == error_mark_node)
7010 return error_mark_node;
7011
7012 /* Convert it to a pointer to the type referred to by the
7013 reference. This will adjust the pointer if a derived to
7014 base conversion is being performed. */
7015 expr = cp_convert (build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (ref_type)),
7016 expr, complain);
7017 /* Convert the pointer to the desired reference type. */
7018 return build_nop (ref_type, expr);
7019 }
7020
7021 case ck_lvalue:
7022 return decay_conversion (expr, complain);
7023
7024 case ck_fnptr:
7025 /* ??? Should the address of a transaction-safe pointer point to the TM
7026 clone, and this conversion look up the primary function? */
7027 return build_nop (totype, expr);
7028
7029 case ck_qual:
7030 /* Warn about deprecated conversion if appropriate. */
7031 string_conv_p (totype, expr, 1);
7032 break;
7033
7034 case ck_ptr:
7035 if (convs->base_p)
7036 expr = convert_to_base (expr, totype, !c_cast_p,
7037 /*nonnull=*/false, complain);
7038 return build_nop (totype, expr);
7039
7040 case ck_pmem:
7041 return convert_ptrmem (totype, expr, /*allow_inverse_p=*/false,
7042 c_cast_p, complain);
7043
7044 default:
7045 break;
7046 }
7047
7048 if (convs->check_narrowing
7049 && !check_narrowing (totype, expr, complain))
7050 return error_mark_node;
7051
7052 if (issue_conversion_warnings)
7053 expr = cp_convert_and_check (totype, expr, complain);
7054 else
7055 expr = cp_convert (totype, expr, complain);
7056
7057 return expr;
7058}
7059
7060/* ARG is being passed to a varargs function. Perform any conversions
7061 required. Return the converted value. */
7062
7063tree
7064convert_arg_to_ellipsis (tree arg, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7065{
7066 tree arg_type;
7067 location_t loc = EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (arg, input_location);
7068
7069 /* [expr.call]
7070
7071 The lvalue-to-rvalue, array-to-pointer, and function-to-pointer
7072 standard conversions are performed. */
7073 arg = decay_conversion (arg, complain);
7074 arg_type = TREE_TYPE (arg);
7075 /* [expr.call]
7076
7077 If the argument has integral or enumeration type that is subject
7078 to the integral promotions (_conv.prom_), or a floating point
7079 type that is subject to the floating point promotion
7080 (_conv.fpprom_), the value of the argument is converted to the
7081 promoted type before the call. */
7082 if (TREE_CODE (arg_type) == REAL_TYPE
7083 && (TYPE_PRECISION (arg_type)
7084 < TYPE_PRECISION (double_type_node))
7085 && !DECIMAL_FLOAT_MODE_P (TYPE_MODE (arg_type)))
7086 {
7087 if ((complain & tf_warning)
7088 && warn_double_promotion && !c_inhibit_evaluation_warnings)
7089 warning_at (loc, OPT_Wdouble_promotion,
7090 "implicit conversion from %qT to %qT when passing "
7091 "argument to function",
7092 arg_type, double_type_node);
7093 arg = convert_to_real_nofold (double_type_node, arg);
7094 }
7095 else if (NULLPTR_TYPE_P (arg_type))
7096 arg = null_pointer_node;
7097 else if (INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (arg_type))
7098 {
7099 if (SCOPED_ENUM_P (arg_type))
7100 {
7101 tree prom = cp_convert (ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (arg_type), arg,
7102 complain);
7103 prom = cp_perform_integral_promotions (prom, complain);
7104 if (abi_version_crosses (6)
7105 && TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (prom)) != TYPE_MODE (arg_type)
7106 && (complain & tf_warning))
7107 warning_at (loc, OPT_Wabi, "scoped enum %qT passed through ... as "
7108 "%qT before -fabi-version=6, %qT after", arg_type,
7109 TREE_TYPE (prom), ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (arg_type));
7110 if (!abi_version_at_least (6))
7111 arg = prom;
7112 }
7113 else
7114 arg = cp_perform_integral_promotions (arg, complain);
7115 }
7116
7117 arg = require_complete_type_sfinae (arg, complain);
7118 arg_type = TREE_TYPE (arg);
7119
7120 if (arg != error_mark_node
7121 /* In a template (or ill-formed code), we can have an incomplete type
7122 even after require_complete_type_sfinae, in which case we don't know
7123 whether it has trivial copy or not. */
7124 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (arg_type)
7125 && !cp_unevaluated_operand)
7126 {
7127 /* [expr.call] 5.2.2/7:
7128 Passing a potentially-evaluated argument of class type (Clause 9)
7129 with a non-trivial copy constructor or a non-trivial destructor
7130 with no corresponding parameter is conditionally-supported, with
7131 implementation-defined semantics.
7132
7133 We support it as pass-by-invisible-reference, just like a normal
7134 value parameter.
7135
7136 If the call appears in the context of a sizeof expression,
7137 it is not potentially-evaluated. */
7138 if (type_has_nontrivial_copy_init (arg_type)
7139 || TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (arg_type))
7140 {
7141 arg = force_rvalue (arg, complain);
7142 if (complain & tf_warning)
7143 warning (OPT_Wconditionally_supported,
7144 "passing objects of non-trivially-copyable "
7145 "type %q#T through %<...%> is conditionally supported",
7146 arg_type);
7147 return build1 (ADDR_EXPR, build_reference_type (arg_type), arg);
7148 }
7149 /* Build up a real lvalue-to-rvalue conversion in case the
7150 copy constructor is trivial but not callable. */
7151 else if (CLASS_TYPE_P (arg_type))
7152 force_rvalue (arg, complain);
7153
7154 }
7155
7156 return arg;
7157}
7158
7159/* va_arg (EXPR, TYPE) is a builtin. Make sure it is not abused. */
7160
7161tree
7162build_x_va_arg (source_location loc, tree expr, tree type)
7163{
7164 if (processing_template_decl)
7165 {
7166 tree r = build_min (VA_ARG_EXPR, type, expr);
7167 SET_EXPR_LOCATION (r, loc);
7168 return r;
7169 }
7170
7171 type = complete_type_or_else (type, NULL_TREE);
7172
7173 if (expr == error_mark_node || !type)
7174 return error_mark_node;
7175
7176 expr = mark_lvalue_use (expr);
7177
7178 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
7179 {
7180 error ("cannot receive reference type %qT through %<...%>", type);
7181 return error_mark_node;
7182 }
7183
7184 if (type_has_nontrivial_copy_init (type)
7185 || TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (type))
7186 {
7187 /* conditionally-supported behavior [expr.call] 5.2.2/7. Let's treat
7188 it as pass by invisible reference. */
7189 warning_at (loc, OPT_Wconditionally_supported,
7190 "receiving objects of non-trivially-copyable type %q#T "
7191 "through %<...%> is conditionally-supported", type);
7192
7193 tree ref = cp_build_reference_type (type, false);
7194 expr = build_va_arg (loc, expr, ref);
7195 return convert_from_reference (expr);
7196 }
7197
7198 tree ret = build_va_arg (loc, expr, type);
7199 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
7200 /* Wrap the VA_ARG_EXPR in a TARGET_EXPR now so other code doesn't need to
7201 know how to handle it. */
7202 ret = get_target_expr (ret);
7203 return ret;
7204}
7205
7206/* TYPE has been given to va_arg. Apply the default conversions which
7207 would have happened when passed via ellipsis. Return the promoted
7208 type, or the passed type if there is no change. */
7209
7210tree
7211cxx_type_promotes_to (tree type)
7212{
7213 tree promote;
7214
7215 /* Perform the array-to-pointer and function-to-pointer
7216 conversions. */
7217 type = type_decays_to (type);
7218
7219 promote = type_promotes_to (type);
7220 if (same_type_p (type, promote))
7221 promote = type;
7222
7223 return promote;
7224}
7225
7226/* ARG is a default argument expression being passed to a parameter of
7227 the indicated TYPE, which is a parameter to FN. PARMNUM is the
7228 zero-based argument number. Do any required conversions. Return
7229 the converted value. */
7230
7231static GTY(()) vec<tree, va_gc> *default_arg_context;
7232void
7233push_defarg_context (tree fn)
7234{ vec_safe_push (default_arg_context, fn); }
7235
7236void
7237pop_defarg_context (void)
7238{ default_arg_context->pop (); }
7239
7240tree
7241convert_default_arg (tree type, tree arg, tree fn, int parmnum,
7242 tsubst_flags_t complain)
7243{
7244 int i;
7245 tree t;
7246
7247 /* See through clones. */
7248 fn = DECL_ORIGIN (fn);
7249 /* And inheriting ctors. */
7250 if (flag_new_inheriting_ctors)
7251 fn = strip_inheriting_ctors (fn);
7252
7253 /* Detect recursion. */
7254 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (default_arg_context, i, t)
7255 if (t == fn)
7256 {
7257 if (complain & tf_error)
7258 error ("recursive evaluation of default argument for %q#D", fn);
7259 return error_mark_node;
7260 }
7261
7262 /* If the ARG is an unparsed default argument expression, the
7263 conversion cannot be performed. */
7264 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == DEFAULT_ARG)
7265 {
7266 if (complain & tf_error)
7267 error ("call to %qD uses the default argument for parameter %P, which "
7268 "is not yet defined", fn, parmnum);
7269 return error_mark_node;
7270 }
7271
7272 push_defarg_context (fn);
7273
7274 if (fn && DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (fn))
7275 arg = tsubst_default_argument (fn, type, arg, complain);
7276
7277 /* Due to:
7278
7279 [dcl.fct.default]
7280
7281 The names in the expression are bound, and the semantic
7282 constraints are checked, at the point where the default
7283 expressions appears.
7284
7285 we must not perform access checks here. */
7286 push_deferring_access_checks (dk_no_check);
7287 /* We must make a copy of ARG, in case subsequent processing
7288 alters any part of it. */
7289 arg = break_out_target_exprs (arg);
7290 arg = convert_for_initialization (0, type, arg, LOOKUP_IMPLICIT,
7291 ICR_DEFAULT_ARGUMENT, fn, parmnum,
7292 complain);
7293 arg = convert_for_arg_passing (type, arg, complain);
7294 pop_deferring_access_checks();
7295
7296 pop_defarg_context ();
7297
7298 return arg;
7299}
7300
7301/* Returns the type which will really be used for passing an argument of
7302 type TYPE. */
7303
7304tree
7305type_passed_as (tree type)
7306{
7307 /* Pass classes with copy ctors by invisible reference. */
7308 if (TREE_ADDRESSABLE (type))
7309 {
7310 type = build_reference_type (type);
7311 /* There are no other pointers to this temporary. */
7312 type = cp_build_qualified_type (type, TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT);
7313 }
7314 else if (targetm.calls.promote_prototypes (type)
7315 && INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (type)
7316 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type)
7317 && tree_int_cst_lt (TYPE_SIZE (type), TYPE_SIZE (integer_type_node)))
7318 type = integer_type_node;
7319
7320 return type;
7321}
7322
7323/* Actually perform the appropriate conversion. */
7324
7325tree
7326convert_for_arg_passing (tree type, tree val, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7327{
7328 tree bitfield_type;
7329
7330 /* If VAL is a bitfield, then -- since it has already been converted
7331 to TYPE -- it cannot have a precision greater than TYPE.
7332
7333 If it has a smaller precision, we must widen it here. For
7334 example, passing "int f:3;" to a function expecting an "int" will
7335 not result in any conversion before this point.
7336
7337 If the precision is the same we must not risk widening. For
7338 example, the COMPONENT_REF for a 32-bit "long long" bitfield will
7339 often have type "int", even though the C++ type for the field is
7340 "long long". If the value is being passed to a function
7341 expecting an "int", then no conversions will be required. But,
7342 if we call convert_bitfield_to_declared_type, the bitfield will
7343 be converted to "long long". */
7344 bitfield_type = is_bitfield_expr_with_lowered_type (val);
7345 if (bitfield_type
7346 && TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (val)) < TYPE_PRECISION (type))
7347 val = convert_to_integer_nofold (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (bitfield_type), val);
7348
7349 if (val == error_mark_node)
7350 ;
7351 /* Pass classes with copy ctors by invisible reference. */
7352 else if (TREE_ADDRESSABLE (type))
7353 val = build1 (ADDR_EXPR, build_reference_type (type), val);
7354 else if (targetm.calls.promote_prototypes (type)
7355 && INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (type)
7356 && COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type)
7357 && tree_int_cst_lt (TYPE_SIZE (type), TYPE_SIZE (integer_type_node)))
7358 val = cp_perform_integral_promotions (val, complain);
7359 if ((complain & tf_warning)
7360 && warn_suggest_attribute_format)
7361 {
7362 tree rhstype = TREE_TYPE (val);
7363 const enum tree_code coder = TREE_CODE (rhstype);
7364 const enum tree_code codel = TREE_CODE (type);
7365 if ((codel == POINTER_TYPE || codel == REFERENCE_TYPE)
7366 && coder == codel
7367 && check_missing_format_attribute (type, rhstype))
7368 warning (OPT_Wsuggest_attribute_format,
7369 "argument of function call might be a candidate for a format attribute");
7370 }
7371 return val;
7372}
7373
7374/* Returns non-zero iff FN is a function with magic varargs, i.e. ones for
7375 which just decay_conversion or no conversions at all should be done.
7376 This is true for some builtins which don't act like normal functions.
7377 Return 2 if no conversions at all should be done, 1 if just
7378 decay_conversion. Return 3 for special treatment of the 3rd argument
7379 for __builtin_*_overflow_p. */
7380
7381int
7382magic_varargs_p (tree fn)
7383{
7384 if (flag_cilkplus && is_cilkplus_reduce_builtin (fn) != BUILT_IN_NONE)
7385 return 2;
7386
7387 if (DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (fn) == BUILT_IN_NORMAL)
7388 switch (DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (fn))
7389 {
7390 case BUILT_IN_CLASSIFY_TYPE:
7391 case BUILT_IN_CONSTANT_P:
7392 case BUILT_IN_NEXT_ARG:
7393 case BUILT_IN_VA_START:
7394 return 1;
7395
7396 case BUILT_IN_ADD_OVERFLOW_P:
7397 case BUILT_IN_SUB_OVERFLOW_P:
7398 case BUILT_IN_MUL_OVERFLOW_P:
7399 return 3;
7400
7401 default:;
7402 return lookup_attribute ("type generic",
7403 TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (TREE_TYPE (fn))) != 0;
7404 }
7405
7406 return 0;
7407}
7408
7409/* Returns the decl of the dispatcher function if FN is a function version. */
7410
7411tree
7412get_function_version_dispatcher (tree fn)
7413{
7414 tree dispatcher_decl = NULL;
7415
7416 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (fn) == FUNCTION_DECL
7417 && DECL_FUNCTION_VERSIONED (fn));
7418
7419 gcc_assert (targetm.get_function_versions_dispatcher);
7420 dispatcher_decl = targetm.get_function_versions_dispatcher (fn);
7421
7422 if (dispatcher_decl == NULL)
7423 {
7424 error_at (input_location, "use of multiversioned function "
7425 "without a default");
7426 return NULL;
7427 }
7428
7429 retrofit_lang_decl (dispatcher_decl);
7430 gcc_assert (dispatcher_decl != NULL);
7431 return dispatcher_decl;
7432}
7433
7434/* fn is a function version dispatcher that is marked used. Mark all the
7435 semantically identical function versions it will dispatch as used. */
7436
7437void
7438mark_versions_used (tree fn)
7439{
7440 struct cgraph_node *node;
7441 struct cgraph_function_version_info *node_v;
7442 struct cgraph_function_version_info *it_v;
7443
7444 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (fn) == FUNCTION_DECL);
7445
7446 node = cgraph_node::get (fn);
7447 if (node == NULL)
7448 return;
7449
7450 gcc_assert (node->dispatcher_function);
7451
7452 node_v = node->function_version ();
7453 if (node_v == NULL)
7454 return;
7455
7456 /* All semantically identical versions are chained. Traverse and mark each
7457 one of them as used. */
7458 it_v = node_v->next;
7459 while (it_v != NULL)
7460 {
7461 mark_used (it_v->this_node->decl);
7462 it_v = it_v->next;
7463 }
7464}
7465
7466/* Build a call to "the copy constructor" for the type of A, even if it
7467 wouldn't be selected by normal overload resolution. Used for
7468 diagnostics. */
7469
7470static tree
7471call_copy_ctor (tree a, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7472{
7473 tree ctype = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (a));
7474 tree binfo = TYPE_BINFO (ctype);
7475 tree copy = get_copy_ctor (ctype, complain);
7476 copy = build_baselink (binfo, binfo, copy, NULL_TREE);
7477 tree ob = build_dummy_object (ctype);
7478 vec<tree, va_gc>* args = make_tree_vector_single (a);
7479 tree r = build_new_method_call (ob, copy, &args, NULL_TREE,
7480 LOOKUP_NORMAL, NULL, complain);
7481 release_tree_vector (args);
7482 return r;
7483}
7484
7485/* Return true iff T refers to a base field. */
7486
7487static bool
7488is_base_field_ref (tree t)
7489{
7490 STRIP_NOPS (t);
7491 if (TREE_CODE (t) == ADDR_EXPR)
7492 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 0);
7493 if (TREE_CODE (t) == COMPONENT_REF)
7494 t = TREE_OPERAND (t, 1);
7495 if (TREE_CODE (t) == FIELD_DECL)
7496 return DECL_FIELD_IS_BASE (t);
7497 return false;
7498}
7499
7500/* We can't elide a copy from a function returning by value to a base
7501 subobject, as the callee might clobber tail padding. Return true iff this
7502 could be that case. */
7503
7504static bool
7505unsafe_copy_elision_p (tree target, tree exp)
7506{
7507 /* Copy elision only happens with a TARGET_EXPR. */
7508 if (TREE_CODE (exp) != TARGET_EXPR)
7509 return false;
7510 tree type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (exp));
7511 /* It's safe to elide the copy for a class with no tail padding. */
7512 if (tree_int_cst_equal (TYPE_SIZE (type), CLASSTYPE_SIZE (type)))
7513 return false;
7514 /* It's safe to elide the copy if we aren't initializing a base object. */
7515 if (!is_base_field_ref (target))
7516 return false;
7517 tree init = TARGET_EXPR_INITIAL (exp);
7518 /* build_compound_expr pushes COMPOUND_EXPR inside TARGET_EXPR. */
7519 while (TREE_CODE (init) == COMPOUND_EXPR)
7520 init = TREE_OPERAND (init, 1);
7521 if (TREE_CODE (init) == COND_EXPR)
7522 {
7523 /* We'll end up copying from each of the arms of the COND_EXPR directly
7524 into the target, so look at them. */
7525 if (tree op = TREE_OPERAND (init, 1))
7526 if (unsafe_copy_elision_p (target, op))
7527 return true;
7528 return unsafe_copy_elision_p (target, TREE_OPERAND (init, 2));
7529 }
7530 return (TREE_CODE (init) == AGGR_INIT_EXPR
7531 && !AGGR_INIT_VIA_CTOR_P (init));
7532}
7533
7534/* Subroutine of the various build_*_call functions. Overload resolution
7535 has chosen a winning candidate CAND; build up a CALL_EXPR accordingly.
7536 ARGS is a TREE_LIST of the unconverted arguments to the call. FLAGS is a
7537 bitmask of various LOOKUP_* flags which apply to the call itself. */
7538
7539static tree
7540build_over_call (struct z_candidate *cand, int flags, tsubst_flags_t complain)
7541{
7542 tree fn = cand->fn;
7543 const vec<tree, va_gc> *args = cand->args;
7544 tree first_arg = cand->first_arg;
7545 conversion **convs = cand->convs;
7546 conversion *conv;
7547 tree parm = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (fn));
7548 int parmlen;
7549 tree val;
7550 int i = 0;
7551 int j = 0;
7552 unsigned int arg_index = 0;
7553 int is_method = 0;
7554 int nargs;
7555 tree *argarray;
7556 bool already_used = false;
7557
7558 /* In a template, there is no need to perform all of the work that
7559 is normally done. We are only interested in the type of the call
7560 expression, i.e., the return type of the function. Any semantic
7561 errors will be deferred until the template is instantiated. */
7562 if (processing_template_decl)
7563 {
