9987 This algorithm has a worst case of O(2n) (winner is last), and a best
9988 case of O(n/2) (totally ambiguous); much better than a sorting
9989 algorithm. */
9990
9991static struct z_candidate *
9992tourney (struct z_candidate *candidates, tsubst_flags_t complain)
9993{
9994 struct z_candidate *champ = candidates, *challenger;
9995 int fate;
9996 int champ_compared_to_predecessor = 0;
9997
9998 /* Walk through the list once, comparing each current champ to the next
9999 candidate, knocking out a candidate or two with each comparison. */
10000
10001 for (challenger = champ->next; challenger; )
10002 {
10003 fate = joust (champ, challenger, 0, complain);
10004 if (fate == 1)
10005 challenger = challenger->next;
10006 else
10007 {
10008 if (fate == 0)
10009 {
10010 champ = challenger->next;
10011 if (champ == 0)
10012 return NULL;
10013 champ_compared_to_predecessor = 0;
10014 }
10015 else
10016 {
10017 champ = challenger;
10018 champ_compared_to_predecessor = 1;
10019 }
10020
10021 challenger = champ->next;
10022 }
10023 }
10024
10025 /* Make sure the champ is better than all the candidates it hasn't yet
10026 been compared to. */
10027
10028 for (challenger = candidates;
10029 challenger != champ
10030 && !(champ_compared_to_predecessor && challenger->next == champ);
10031 challenger = challenger->next)
10032 {
10033 fate = joust (champ, challenger, 0, complain);
10034 if (fate != 1)
10035 return NULL;
10036 }
10037
10038 return champ;
10039}
10040
10041/* Returns nonzero if things of type FROM can be converted to TO. */
10042
10043bool
10044can_convert (tree to, tree from, tsubst_flags_t complain)
10045{
10046 tree arg = NULL_TREE;
10047 /* implicit_conversion only considers user-defined conversions
10048 if it has an expression for the call argument list. */
10049 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (from) || CLASS_TYPE_P (to))
10050 arg = build1 (CAST_EXPR, from, NULL_TREE);
10051 return can_convert_arg (to, from, arg, LOOKUP_IMPLICIT, complain);
10052}
10053
10054/* Returns nonzero if things of type FROM can be converted to TO with a
10055 standard conversion. */
10056
10057bool
10058can_convert_standard (tree to, tree from, tsubst_flags_t complain)
10059{
10060 return can_convert_arg (to, from, NULL_TREE, LOOKUP_IMPLICIT, complain);
10061}
10062
10063/* Returns nonzero if ARG (of type FROM) can be converted to TO. */
10064
10065bool
10066can_convert_arg (tree to, tree from, tree arg, int flags,
10067 tsubst_flags_t complain)
10068{
10069 conversion *t;
10070 void *p;
10071 bool ok_p;
10072
10073 /* Get the high-water mark for the CONVERSION_OBSTACK. */
10074 p = conversion_obstack_alloc (0);
10075 /* We want to discard any access checks done for this test,
10076 as we might not be in the appropriate access context and
10077 we'll do the check again when we actually perform the
10078 conversion. */
10079 push_deferring_access_checks (dk_deferred);
10080
10081 t = implicit_conversion (to, from, arg, /*c_cast_p=*/false,
10082 flags, complain);
10083 ok_p = (t && !t->bad_p);
10084
10085 /* Discard the access checks now. */
10086 pop_deferring_access_checks ();
10087 /* Free all the conversions we allocated. */
10088 obstack_free (&conversion_obstack, p);
10089
10090 return ok_p;
10091}
10092
10093/* Like can_convert_arg, but allows dubious conversions as well. */
10094
10095bool
10096can_convert_arg_bad (tree to, tree from, tree arg, int flags,
10097 tsubst_flags_t complain)
10098{
10099 conversion *t;
10100 void *p;
10101
10102 /* Get the high-water mark for the CONVERSION_OBSTACK. */
10103 p = conversion_obstack_alloc (0);
10104 /* Try to perform the conversion. */
10105 t = implicit_conversion (to, from, arg, /*c_cast_p=*/false,
10106 flags, complain);
10107 /* Free all the conversions we allocated. */
10108 obstack_free (&conversion_obstack, p);
10109
10110 return t != NULL;
10111}
10112
10113/* Convert EXPR to TYPE. Return the converted expression.
10114
10115 Note that we allow bad conversions here because by the time we get to
10116 this point we are committed to doing the conversion. If we end up
10117 doing a bad conversion, convert_like will complain. */
10118
10119tree
10120perform_implicit_conversion_flags (tree type, tree expr,
10121 tsubst_flags_t complain, int flags)
10122{
10123 conversion *conv;
10124 void *p;
10125 location_t loc = EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (expr, input_location);
10126
10127 if (error_operand_p (expr))
10128 return error_mark_node;
10129
10130 /* Get the high-water mark for the CONVERSION_OBSTACK. */
10131 p = conversion_obstack_alloc (0);
10132
10133 conv = implicit_conversion (type, TREE_TYPE (expr), expr,
10134 /*c_cast_p=*/false,
10135 flags, complain);
10136
10137 if (!conv)
10138 {
10139 if (complain & tf_error)
10140 {
10141 /* If expr has unknown type, then it is an overloaded function.
10142 Call instantiate_type to get good error messages. */
10143 if (TREE_TYPE (expr) == unknown_type_node)
10144 instantiate_type (type, expr, complain);
10145 else if (invalid_nonstatic_memfn_p (loc, expr, complain))
10146 /* We gave an error. */;
10147 else
10148 error_at (loc, "could not convert %qE from %qT to %qT", expr,
10149 TREE_TYPE (expr), type);
10150 }
10151 expr = error_mark_node;
10152 }
10153 else if (processing_template_decl && conv->kind != ck_identity)
10154 {
10155 /* In a template, we are only concerned about determining the
10156 type of non-dependent expressions, so we do not have to
10157 perform the actual conversion. But for initializers, we
10158 need to be able to perform it at instantiation
10159 (or instantiate_non_dependent_expr) time. */
10160 expr = build1 (IMPLICIT_CONV_EXPR, type, expr);
10161 if (!(flags & LOOKUP_ONLYCONVERTING))
10162 IMPLICIT_CONV_EXPR_DIRECT_INIT (expr) = true;
10163 }
10164 else
10165 expr = convert_like (conv, expr, complain);
10166
10167 /* Free all the conversions we allocated. */
10168 obstack_free (&conversion_obstack, p);
10169
10170 return expr;
10171}
10172
10173tree
10174perform_implicit_conversion (tree type, tree expr, tsubst_flags_t complain)
10175{
10176 return perform_implicit_conversion_flags (type, expr, complain,
10177 LOOKUP_IMPLICIT);
10178}
10179
10180/* Convert EXPR to TYPE (as a direct-initialization) if that is
10181 permitted. If the conversion is valid, the converted expression is
10182 returned. Otherwise, NULL_TREE is returned, except in the case
10183 that TYPE is a class type; in that case, an error is issued. If
10184 C_CAST_P is true, then this direct-initialization is taking
10185 place as part of a static_cast being attempted as part of a C-style
10186 cast. */
10187
10188tree
10189perform_direct_initialization_if_possible (tree type,
10190 tree expr,
10191 bool c_cast_p,
10192 tsubst_flags_t complain)
10193{
10194 conversion *conv;
10195 void *p;
10196
10197 if (type == error_mark_node || error_operand_p (expr))
10198 return error_mark_node;
10199 /* [dcl.init]
10200
10201 If the destination type is a (possibly cv-qualified) class type:
10202
10203 -- If the initialization is direct-initialization ...,
10204 constructors are considered. ... If no constructor applies, or
10205 the overload resolution is ambiguous, the initialization is
10206 ill-formed. */
10207 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
10208 {
10209 vec<tree, va_gc> *args = make_tree_vector_single (expr);
10210 expr = build_special_member_call (NULL_TREE, complete_ctor_identifier,
10211 &args, type, LOOKUP_NORMAL, complain);
10212 release_tree_vector (args);
10213 return build_cplus_new (type, expr, complain);
10214 }
10215
10216 /* Get the high-water mark for the CONVERSION_OBSTACK. */
10217 p = conversion_obstack_alloc (0);
10218
10219 conv = implicit_conversion (type, TREE_TYPE (expr), expr,
10220 c_cast_p,
10221 LOOKUP_NORMAL, complain);
10222 if (!conv || conv->bad_p)
10223 expr = NULL_TREE;
10224 else
10225 expr = convert_like_real (conv, expr, NULL_TREE, 0, 0,
10226 /*issue_conversion_warnings=*/false,
10227 c_cast_p,
10228 complain);
10229
10230 /* Free all the conversions we allocated. */
10231 obstack_free (&conversion_obstack, p);
10232
10233 return expr;
10234}
10235
10236/* When initializing a reference that lasts longer than a full-expression,
10237 this special rule applies:
10238
10239 [class.temporary]
10240
10241 The temporary to which the reference is bound or the temporary
10242 that is the complete object to which the reference is bound
10243 persists for the lifetime of the reference.
10244
10245 The temporaries created during the evaluation of the expression
10246 initializing the reference, except the temporary to which the
10247 reference is bound, are destroyed at the end of the
10248 full-expression in which they are created.
10249
10250 In that case, we store the converted expression into a new
10251 VAR_DECL in a new scope.
10252
10253 However, we want to be careful not to create temporaries when
10254 they are not required. For example, given:
10255
10256 struct B {};
10257 struct D : public B {};
10258 D f();
10259 const B& b = f();
10260
10261 there is no need to copy the return value from "f"; we can just
10262 extend its lifetime. Similarly, given:
10263
10264 struct S {};
10265 struct T { operator S(); };
10266 T t;
10267 const S& s = t;
10268
10269 we can extend the lifetime of the return value of the conversion
10270 operator.
10271
10272 The next several functions are involved in this lifetime extension. */
10273
10274/* DECL is a VAR_DECL or FIELD_DECL whose type is a REFERENCE_TYPE. The
10275 reference is being bound to a temporary. Create and return a new
10276 VAR_DECL with the indicated TYPE; this variable will store the value to
10277 which the reference is bound. */
10278
10279tree
10280make_temporary_var_for_ref_to_temp (tree decl, tree type)
10281{
10282 tree var;
10283
10284 /* Create the variable. */
10285 var = create_temporary_var (type);
10286
10287 /* Register the variable. */
10288 if (VAR_P (decl)
10289 && (TREE_STATIC (decl) || CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl)))
10290 {
10291 /* Namespace-scope or local static; give it a mangled name. */
10292 /* FIXME share comdat with decl? */
10293 tree name;
10294
10295 TREE_STATIC (var) = TREE_STATIC (decl);
10296 CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (var) = CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl);
10297 set_decl_tls_model (var, DECL_TLS_MODEL (decl));
10298 name = mangle_ref_init_variable (decl);
10299 DECL_NAME (var) = name;
10300 SET_DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (var, name);
10301 var = pushdecl_top_level (var);
10302 }
10303 else
10304 /* Create a new cleanup level if necessary. */
10305 maybe_push_cleanup_level (type);
10306
10307 return var;
10308}
10309
10310/* EXPR is the initializer for a variable DECL of reference or
10311 std::initializer_list type. Create, push and return a new VAR_DECL
10312 for the initializer so that it will live as long as DECL. Any
10313 cleanup for the new variable is returned through CLEANUP, and the
10314 code to initialize the new variable is returned through INITP. */
10315
10316static tree
10317set_up_extended_ref_temp (tree decl, tree expr, vec<tree, va_gc> **cleanups,
10318 tree *initp)
10319{
10320 tree init;
10321 tree type;
10322 tree var;
10323
10324 /* Create the temporary variable. */
10325 type = TREE_TYPE (expr);
10326 var = make_temporary_var_for_ref_to_temp (decl, type);
10327 layout_decl (var, 0);
10328 /* If the rvalue is the result of a function call it will be
10329 a TARGET_EXPR. If it is some other construct (such as a
10330 member access expression where the underlying object is
10331 itself the result of a function call), turn it into a
10332 TARGET_EXPR here. It is important that EXPR be a
10333 TARGET_EXPR below since otherwise the INIT_EXPR will
10334 attempt to make a bitwise copy of EXPR to initialize
10335 VAR. */
10336 if (TREE_CODE (expr) != TARGET_EXPR)
10337 expr = get_target_expr (expr);
10338
10339 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FIELD_DECL
10340 && extra_warnings && !TREE_NO_WARNING (decl))
10341 {
10342 warning (OPT_Wextra, "a temporary bound to %qD only persists "
10343 "until the constructor exits", decl);
10344 TREE_NO_WARNING (decl) = true;
10345 }
10346
10347 /* Recursively extend temps in this initializer. */
10348 TARGET_EXPR_INITIAL (expr)
10349 = extend_ref_init_temps (decl, TARGET_EXPR_INITIAL (expr), cleanups);
10350
10351 /* Any reference temp has a non-trivial initializer. */
10352 DECL_NONTRIVIALLY_INITIALIZED_P (var) = true;
10353
10354 /* If the initializer is constant, put it in DECL_INITIAL so we get
10355 static initialization and use in constant expressions. */
10356 init = maybe_constant_init (expr);
10357 if (TREE_CONSTANT (init))
10358 {
10359 if (literal_type_p (type) && CP_TYPE_CONST_NON_VOLATILE_P (type))
10360 {
10361 /* 5.19 says that a constant expression can include an
10362 lvalue-rvalue conversion applied to "a glvalue of literal type
10363 that refers to a non-volatile temporary object initialized
10364 with a constant expression". Rather than try to communicate
10365 that this VAR_DECL is a temporary, just mark it constexpr.
10366
10367 Currently this is only useful for initializer_list temporaries,
10368 since reference vars can't appear in constant expressions. */
10369 DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (var) = true;
10370 DECL_INITIALIZED_BY_CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_P (var) = true;
10371 TREE_CONSTANT (var) = true;
10372 }
10373 DECL_INITIAL (var) = init;
10374 init = NULL_TREE;
10375 }
10376 else
10377 /* Create the INIT_EXPR that will initialize the temporary
10378 variable. */
10379 init = split_nonconstant_init (var, expr);
10380 if (at_function_scope_p ())
10381 {
10382 add_decl_expr (var);
10383
10384 if (TREE_STATIC (var))
10385 init = add_stmt_to_compound (init, register_dtor_fn (var));
10386 else
10387 {
10388 tree cleanup = cxx_maybe_build_cleanup (var, tf_warning_or_error);
10389 if (cleanup)
10390 vec_safe_push (*cleanups, cleanup);
10391 }
10392
10393 /* We must be careful to destroy the temporary only
10394 after its initialization has taken place. If the
10395 initialization throws an exception, then the
10396 destructor should not be run. We cannot simply
10397 transform INIT into something like:
10398
10399 (INIT, ({ CLEANUP_STMT; }))
10400
10401 because emit_local_var always treats the
10402 initializer as a full-expression. Thus, the
10403 destructor would run too early; it would run at the
10404 end of initializing the reference variable, rather
10405 than at the end of the block enclosing the
10406 reference variable.
10407
10408 The solution is to pass back a cleanup expression
10409 which the caller is responsible for attaching to
10410 the statement tree. */
10411 }
10412 else
10413 {
10414 rest_of_decl_compilation (var, /*toplev=*/1, at_eof);
10415 if (TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (type))
10416 {
10417 if (CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (var))
10418 tls_aggregates = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, var,
10419 tls_aggregates);
10420 else
10421 static_aggregates = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, var,
10422 static_aggregates);
10423 }
10424 else
10425 /* Check whether the dtor is callable. */
10426 cxx_maybe_build_cleanup (var, tf_warning_or_error);
10427 }
10428 /* Avoid -Wunused-variable warning (c++/38958). */
10429 if (TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (type)
10430 && VAR_P (decl))
10431 TREE_USED (decl) = DECL_READ_P (decl) = true;
10432
10433 *initp = init;
10434 return var;
10435}
10436
10437/* Convert EXPR to the indicated reference TYPE, in a way suitable for
10438 initializing a variable of that TYPE. */
10439
10440tree
10441initialize_reference (tree type, tree expr,
10442 int flags, tsubst_flags_t complain)
10443{
10444 conversion *conv;
10445 void *p;
10446 location_t loc = EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (expr, input_location);
10447
10448 if (type == error_mark_node || error_operand_p (expr))
10449 return error_mark_node;
10450
10451 /* Get the high-water mark for the CONVERSION_OBSTACK. */
10452 p = conversion_obstack_alloc (0);
10453
10454 conv = reference_binding (type, TREE_TYPE (expr), expr, /*c_cast_p=*/false,
10455 flags, complain);
10456 if (!conv || conv->bad_p)
10457 {
10458 if (complain & tf_error)
10459 {
10460 if (conv)
10461 convert_like (conv, expr, complain);
10462 else if (!CP_TYPE_CONST_P (TREE_TYPE (type))
10463 && !TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (type)
10464 && !lvalue_p (expr))
10465 error_at (loc, "invalid initialization of non-const reference of "
10466 "type %qT from an rvalue of type %qT",
10467 type, TREE_TYPE (expr));
10468 else
10469 error_at (loc, "invalid initialization of reference of type "
10470 "%qT from expression of type %qT", type,
10471 TREE_TYPE (expr));
10472 }
10473 return error_mark_node;
10474 }
10475
10476 if (conv->kind == ck_ref_bind)
10477 /* Perform the conversion. */
10478 expr = convert_like (conv, expr, complain);
10479 else if (conv->kind == ck_ambig)
10480 /* We gave an error in build_user_type_conversion_1. */
10481 expr = error_mark_node;
10482 else
10483 gcc_unreachable ();
10484
10485 /* Free all the conversions we allocated. */
10486 obstack_free (&conversion_obstack, p);
10487
10488 return expr;
10489}
10490
10491/* Subroutine of extend_ref_init_temps. Possibly extend one initializer,
10492 which is bound either to a reference or a std::initializer_list. */
10493
10494static tree
10495extend_ref_init_temps_1 (tree decl, tree init, vec<tree, va_gc> **cleanups)
10496{
10497 tree sub = init;
10498 tree *p;
10499 STRIP_NOPS (sub);
10500 if (TREE_CODE (sub) == COMPOUND_EXPR)
10501 {
10502 TREE_OPERAND (sub, 1)
10503 = extend_ref_init_temps_1 (decl, TREE_OPERAND (sub, 1), cleanups);
10504 return init;
10505 }
10506 if (TREE_CODE (sub) != ADDR_EXPR)
10507 return init;
10508 /* Deal with binding to a subobject. */
10509 for (p = &TREE_OPERAND (sub, 0); TREE_CODE (*p) == COMPONENT_REF; )
10510 p = &TREE_OPERAND (*p, 0);
10511 if (TREE_CODE (*p) == TARGET_EXPR)
10512 {
10513 tree subinit = NULL_TREE;
10514 *p = set_up_extended_ref_temp (decl, *p, cleanups, &subinit);
10515 recompute_tree_invariant_for_addr_expr (sub);
10516 if (init != sub)
10517 init = fold_convert (TREE_TYPE (init), sub);
10518 if (subinit)
10519 init = build2 (COMPOUND_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (init), subinit, init);
10520 }
10521 return init;
10522}
10523
10524/* INIT is part of the initializer for DECL. If there are any
10525 reference or initializer lists being initialized, extend their
10526 lifetime to match that of DECL. */
10527
10528tree
10529extend_ref_init_temps (tree decl, tree init, vec<tree, va_gc> **cleanups)
10530{
10531 tree type = TREE_TYPE (init);
10532 if (processing_template_decl)
10533 return init;
10534 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
10535 init = extend_ref_init_temps_1 (decl, init, cleanups);
10536 else
10537 {
10538 tree ctor = init;
10539 if (TREE_CODE (ctor) == TARGET_EXPR)
10540 ctor = TARGET_EXPR_INITIAL (ctor);
10541 if (TREE_CODE (ctor) == CONSTRUCTOR)
10542 {
10543 if (is_std_init_list (type))
10544 {
10545 /* The temporary array underlying a std::initializer_list
10546 is handled like a reference temporary. */
10547 tree array = CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (ctor, 0)->value;
10548 array = extend_ref_init_temps_1 (decl, array, cleanups);
10549 CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (ctor, 0)->value = array;
10550 }
10551 else
10552 {
10553 unsigned i;
10554 constructor_elt *p;
10555 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *elts = CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (ctor);
10556 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (elts, i, p)
10557 p->value = extend_ref_init_temps (decl, p->value, cleanups);
10558 }
10559 }
10560 }
10561
10562 return init;
10563}
10564
10565/* Returns true iff an initializer for TYPE could contain temporaries that
10566 need to be extended because they are bound to references or
10567 std::initializer_list. */
10568
10569bool
10570type_has_extended_temps (tree type)
10571{
10572 type = strip_array_types (type);
10573 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
10574 return true;
10575 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
10576 {
10577 if (is_std_init_list (type))
10578 return true;
10579 for (tree f = next_initializable_field (TYPE_FIELDS (type));
10580 f; f = next_initializable_field (DECL_CHAIN (f)))
10581 if (type_has_extended_temps (TREE_TYPE (f)))
10582 return true;
10583 }
10584 return false;
10585}
10586
10587/* Returns true iff TYPE is some variant of std::initializer_list. */
10588
10589bool
10590is_std_init_list (tree type)
10591{
10592 /* Look through typedefs. */
10593 if (!TYPE_P (type))
10594 return false;
10595 if (cxx_dialect == cxx98)
10596 return false;
10597 type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type);
10598 return (CLASS_TYPE_P (type)
10599 && CP_TYPE_CONTEXT (type) == std_node
10600 && strcmp (TYPE_NAME_STRING (type), "initializer_list") == 0);
10601}
10602
10603/* Returns true iff DECL is a list constructor: i.e. a constructor which
10604 will accept an argument list of a single std::initializer_list<T>. */
10605
10606bool
10607is_list_ctor (tree decl)
10608{
10609 tree args = FUNCTION_FIRST_USER_PARMTYPE (decl);
10610 tree arg;
10611
10612 if (!args || args == void_list_node)
10613 return false;
10614
10615 arg = non_reference (TREE_VALUE (args));
10616 if (!is_std_init_list (arg))
10617 return false;
10618
10619 args = TREE_CHAIN (args);
10620
10621 if (args && args != void_list_node && !TREE_PURPOSE (args))
10622 /* There are more non-defaulted parms. */
10623 return false;
10624
10625 return true;
10626}
